198/* Terminology:
199 * qp = h.264's quantizer
200 * qscale = linearized quantizer = Lagrange multiplier
201 */
202static inline float qp2qscale( float qp )
203{
204 return 0.85f * powf( 2.0f, ( qp - (12.0f + QP_BD_OFFSET) ) / 6.0f );
205}
206static inline float qscale2qp( float qscale )
207{
208 return (12.0f + QP_BD_OFFSET) + 6.0f * log2f( qscale/0.85f );
209}
210
211/* Texture bitrate is not quite inversely proportional to qscale,
212 * probably due the the changing number of SKIP blocks.
213 * MV bits level off at about qp<=12, because the lambda used
214 * for motion estimation is constant there. */
215static inline double qscale2bits( ratecontrol_entry_t *rce, double qscale )
216{
217 if( qscale<0.1 )
218 qscale = 0.1;
219 return (rce->tex_bits + .1) * pow( rce->qscale / qscale, 1.1 )
220 + rce->mv_bits * pow( X264_MAX(rce->qscale, 1) / X264_MAX(qscale, 1), 0.5 )
221 + rce->misc_bits;
222}

224static ALWAYS_INLINE uint32_t ac_energy_var( uint64_t sum_ssd, int shift, x264_frame_t *frame, int i, int b_store )
225{
226 uint32_t sum = sum_ssd;
227 uint32_t ssd = sum_ssd >> 32;
228 if( b_store )
229 {
230 frame->i_pixel_sum[i] += sum;
231 frame->i_pixel_ssd[i] += ssd;
232 }
233 return ssd - ((uint64_t)sum * sum >> shift);
234}
235
236static ALWAYS_INLINE uint32_t ac_energy_plane( x264_t *h, int mb_x, int mb_y, x264_frame_t *frame, int i, int b_chroma, int b_field, int b_store )
237{
238 int height = b_chroma ? 16>>CHROMA_V_SHIFT : 16;
239 int stride = frame->i_stride[i];
240 int offset = b_field
241 ? 16 * mb_x + height * (mb_y&~1) * stride + (mb_y&1) * stride
242 : 16 * mb_x + height * mb_y * stride;
243 stride <<= b_field;
244 if( b_chroma )
245 {
246 ALIGNED_ARRAY_64( pixel, pix,[FENC_STRIDE*16] );
247 int chromapix = h->luma2chroma_pixel[PIXEL_16x16];
248 int shift = 7 - CHROMA_V_SHIFT;
249
250 h->mc.load_deinterleave_chroma_fenc( pix, frame->plane[1] + offset, stride, height );
251 return ac_energy_var( h->pixf.var[chromapix]( pix, FENC_STRIDE ), shift, frame, 1, b_store )
252 + ac_energy_var( h->pixf.var[chromapix]( pix+FENC_STRIDE/2, FENC_STRIDE ), shift, frame, 2, b_store );
253 }
254 else
255 return ac_energy_var( h->pixf.var[PIXEL_16x16]( frame->plane[i] + offset, stride ), 8, frame, i, b_store );
256}
257
258// Find the total AC energy of the block in all planes.
259static NOINLINE uint32_t ac_energy_mb( x264_t *h, int mb_x, int mb_y, x264_frame_t *frame )
260{
261 /* This function contains annoying hacks because GCC has a habit of reordering emms
262 * and putting it after floating point ops. As a result, we put the emms at the end of the
263 * function and make sure that its always called before the float math. Noinline makes
264 * sure no reordering goes on. */
265 uint32_t var;
266 x264_prefetch_fenc( h, frame, mb_x, mb_y );
267 if( h->mb.b_adaptive_mbaff )
268 {
269 /* We don't know the super-MB mode we're going to pick yet, so
270 * simply try both and pick the lower of the two. */
271 uint32_t var_interlaced, var_progressive;
272 var_interlaced = ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 0, 0, 1, 1 );
273 var_progressive = ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 0, 0, 0, 0 );
274 if( CHROMA444 )
275 {
276 var_interlaced += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 1, 0, 1, 1 );
277 var_progressive += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 1, 0, 0, 0 );
278 var_interlaced += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 2, 0, 1, 1 );
279 var_progressive += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 2, 0, 0, 0 );
280 }
281 else if( CHROMA_FORMAT )
282 {
283 var_interlaced += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 1, 1, 1, 1 );
284 var_progressive += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 1, 1, 0, 0 );
285 }
286 var = X264_MIN( var_interlaced, var_progressive );
287 }
288 else
289 {
290 var = ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 0, 0, PARAM_INTERLACED, 1 );
291 if( CHROMA444 )
292 {
293 var += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 1, 0, PARAM_INTERLACED, 1 );
294 var += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 2, 0, PARAM_INTERLACED, 1 );
295 }
296 else if( CHROMA_FORMAT )
297 var += ac_energy_plane( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame, 1, 1, PARAM_INTERLACED, 1 );
298 }
299 x264_emms();
300 return var;
301}
302
303void x264_adaptive_quant_frame( x264_t *h, x264_frame_t *frame, float *quant_offsets )
304{
305 /* Initialize frame stats */
306 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
307 {
308 frame->i_pixel_sum[i] = 0;
309 frame->i_pixel_ssd[i] = 0;
310 }
311
312 /* Degenerate cases */
313 if( h->param.rc.i_aq_mode == X264_AQ_NONE || h->param.rc.f_aq_strength == 0 )
314 {
315 /* Need to init it anyways for MB tree */
316 if( h->param.rc.i_aq_mode && h->param.rc.f_aq_strength == 0 )
317 {
318 if( quant_offsets )
319 {
320 for( int mb_xy = 0; mb_xy < h->mb.i_mb_count; mb_xy++ )
321 frame->f_qp_offset[mb_xy] = frame->f_qp_offset_aq[mb_xy] = quant_offsets[mb_xy];
322 if( h->frames.b_have_lowres )
323 for( int mb_xy = 0; mb_xy < h->mb.i_mb_count; mb_xy++ )
324 frame->i_inv_qscale_factor[mb_xy] = x264_exp2fix8( frame->f_qp_offset[mb_xy] );
325 }
326 else
327 {
328 memset( frame->f_qp_offset, 0, h->mb.i_mb_count * sizeof(float) );
329 memset( frame->f_qp_offset_aq, 0, h->mb.i_mb_count * sizeof(float) );
330 if( h->frames.b_have_lowres )
331 for( int mb_xy = 0; mb_xy < h->mb.i_mb_count; mb_xy++ )
332 frame->i_inv_qscale_factor[mb_xy] = 256;
333 }
334 }
335 /* Need variance data for weighted prediction */
336 if( h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred )
337 {
338 for( int mb_y = 0; mb_y < h->mb.i_mb_height; mb_y++ )
339 for( int mb_x = 0; mb_x < h->mb.i_mb_width; mb_x++ )
340 ac_energy_mb( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame );
341 }
342 else
343 return;
344 }
345 /* Actual adaptive quantization */
346 else
347 {
348 /* constants chosen to result in approximately the same overall bitrate as without AQ.
349 * FIXME: while they're written in 5 significant digits, they're only tuned to 2. */
350 float strength;
351 float avg_adj = 0.f;
352 float bias_strength = 0.f;
353
354 if( h->param.rc.i_aq_mode == X264_AQ_AUTOVARIANCE || h->param.rc.i_aq_mode == X264_AQ_AUTOVARIANCE_BIASED )
355 {
356 float bit_depth_correction = 1.f / (1 << (2*(BIT_DEPTH-8)));
357 float avg_adj_pow2 = 0.f;
358 for( int mb_y = 0; mb_y < h->mb.i_mb_height; mb_y++ )
359 for( int mb_x = 0; mb_x < h->mb.i_mb_width; mb_x++ )
360 {
361 uint32_t energy = ac_energy_mb( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame );
362 float qp_adj = powf( energy * bit_depth_correction + 1, 0.125f );
363 frame->f_qp_offset[mb_x + mb_y*h->mb.i_mb_stride] = qp_adj;
364 avg_adj += qp_adj;
365 avg_adj_pow2 += qp_adj * qp_adj;
366 }
367 avg_adj /= h->mb.i_mb_count;
368 avg_adj_pow2 /= h->mb.i_mb_count;
369 strength = h->param.rc.f_aq_strength * avg_adj;
370 avg_adj = avg_adj - 0.5f * (avg_adj_pow2 - 14.f) / avg_adj;
371 bias_strength = h->param.rc.f_aq_strength;
372 }
373 else
374 strength = h->param.rc.f_aq_strength * 1.0397f;
375
376 for( int mb_y = 0; mb_y < h->mb.i_mb_height; mb_y++ )
377 for( int mb_x = 0; mb_x < h->mb.i_mb_width; mb_x++ )
378 {
379 float qp_adj;
380 int mb_xy = mb_x + mb_y*h->mb.i_mb_stride;
381 if( h->param.rc.i_aq_mode == X264_AQ_AUTOVARIANCE_BIASED )
382 {
383 qp_adj = frame->f_qp_offset[mb_xy];
384 qp_adj = strength * (qp_adj - avg_adj) + bias_strength * (1.f - 14.f / (qp_adj * qp_adj));
385 }
386 else if( h->param.rc.i_aq_mode == X264_AQ_AUTOVARIANCE )
387 {
388 qp_adj = frame->f_qp_offset[mb_xy];
389 qp_adj = strength * (qp_adj - avg_adj);
390 }
391 else
392 {
393 uint32_t energy = ac_energy_mb( h, mb_x, mb_y, frame );
394 qp_adj = strength * (x264_log2( X264_MAX(energy, 1) ) - (14.427f + 2*(BIT_DEPTH-8)));
395 }
396 if( quant_offsets )
397 qp_adj += quant_offsets[mb_xy];
398 frame->f_qp_offset[mb_xy] =
399 frame->f_qp_offset_aq[mb_xy] = qp_adj;
400 if( h->frames.b_have_lowres )
401 frame->i_inv_qscale_factor[mb_xy] = x264_exp2fix8(qp_adj);
402 }
403 }
404
405 /* Remove mean from SSD calculation */
406 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
407 {
408 uint64_t ssd = frame->i_pixel_ssd[i];
409 uint64_t sum = frame->i_pixel_sum[i];
410 int width = 16*h->mb.i_mb_width >> (i && CHROMA_H_SHIFT);
411 int height = 16*h->mb.i_mb_height >> (i && CHROMA_V_SHIFT);
412 frame->i_pixel_ssd[i] = ssd - (sum * sum + width * height / 2) / (width * height);
413 }
414}

416static int macroblock_tree_rescale_init( x264_t *h, x264_ratecontrol_t *rc )
417{
418 /* Use fractional QP array dimensions to compensate for edge padding */
419 float srcdim[2] = {rc->mbtree.srcdim[0] / 16.f, rc->mbtree.srcdim[1] / 16.f};
420 float dstdim[2] = { h->param.i_width / 16.f, h->param.i_height / 16.f};
421 int srcdimi[2] = {ceil(srcdim[0]), ceil(srcdim[1])};
422 int dstdimi[2] = {ceil(dstdim[0]), ceil(dstdim[1])};
423 if( h->param.b_interlaced || h->param.b_fake_interlaced )
424 {
425 srcdimi[1] = (srcdimi[1]+1)&~1;
426 dstdimi[1] = (dstdimi[1]+1)&~1;
427 }
428
429 rc->mbtree.src_mb_count = srcdimi[0] * srcdimi[1];
430
431 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->mbtree.qp_buffer[0], rc->mbtree.src_mb_count * sizeof(uint16_t) );
432 if( h->param.i_bframe_pyramid && h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
433 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->mbtree.qp_buffer[1], rc->mbtree.src_mb_count * sizeof(uint16_t) );
434 rc->mbtree.qpbuf_pos = -1;
435
436 /* No rescaling to do */
437 if( srcdimi[0] == dstdimi[0] && srcdimi[1] == dstdimi[1] )
438 return 0;
439
440 rc->mbtree.rescale_enabled = 1;
441
442 /* Allocate intermediate scaling buffers */
443 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->mbtree.scale_buffer[0], srcdimi[0] * srcdimi[1] * sizeof(float) );
444 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->mbtree.scale_buffer[1], dstdimi[0] * srcdimi[1] * sizeof(float) );
445
446 /* Allocate and calculate resize filter parameters and coefficients */
447 for( int i = 0; i < 2; i++ )
448 {
449 if( srcdim[i] > dstdim[i] ) // downscale
450 rc->mbtree.filtersize[i] = 1 + (2 * srcdimi[i] + dstdimi[i] - 1) / dstdimi[i];
451 else // upscale
452 rc->mbtree.filtersize[i] = 3;
453
454 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->mbtree.coeffs[i], rc->mbtree.filtersize[i] * dstdimi[i] * sizeof(float) );
455 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->mbtree.pos[i], dstdimi[i] * sizeof(int) );
456
457 /* Initialize filter coefficients */
458 float inc = srcdim[i] / dstdim[i];
459 float dmul = inc > 1.f ? dstdim[i] / srcdim[i] : 1.f;
460 float dstinsrc = 0.5f * inc - 0.5f;
461 int filtersize = rc->mbtree.filtersize[i];
462 for( int j = 0; j < dstdimi[i]; j++ )
463 {
464 int pos = dstinsrc - (filtersize - 2.f) * 0.5f;
465 float sum = 0.0;
466 rc->mbtree.pos[i][j] = pos;
467 for( int k = 0; k < filtersize; k++ )
468 {
469 float d = fabs( pos + k - dstinsrc ) * dmul;
470 float coeff = X264_MAX( 1.f - d, 0 );
471 rc->mbtree.coeffs[i][j * filtersize + k] = coeff;
472 sum += coeff;
473 }
474 sum = 1.0f / sum;
475 for( int k = 0; k < filtersize; k++ )
476 rc->mbtree.coeffs[i][j * filtersize + k] *= sum;
477 dstinsrc += inc;
478 }
479 }
480
481 /* Write back actual qp array dimensions */
482 rc->mbtree.srcdim[0] = srcdimi[0];
483 rc->mbtree.srcdim[1] = srcdimi[1];
484 return 0;
485fail:
486 return -1;
487}
488
489static void macroblock_tree_rescale_destroy( x264_ratecontrol_t *rc )
490{
491 for( int i = 0; i < 2; i++ )
492 {
493 x264_free( rc->mbtree.qp_buffer[i] );
494 x264_free( rc->mbtree.scale_buffer[i] );
495 x264_free( rc->mbtree.coeffs[i] );
496 x264_free( rc->mbtree.pos[i] );
497 }
498}
499
500static ALWAYS_INLINE float tapfilter( float *src, int pos, int max, int stride, float *coeff, int filtersize )
501{
502 float sum = 0.f;
503 for( int i = 0; i < filtersize; i++, pos++ )
504 sum += src[x264_clip3( pos, 0, max-1 )*stride] * coeff[i];
505 return sum;
506}
507
508static void macroblock_tree_rescale( x264_t *h, x264_ratecontrol_t *rc, float *dst )
509{
510 float *input, *output;
511 int filtersize, stride, height;
512
513 /* H scale first */
514 input = rc->mbtree.scale_buffer[0];
515 output = rc->mbtree.scale_buffer[1];
516 filtersize = rc->mbtree.filtersize[0];
517 stride = rc->mbtree.srcdim[0];
518 height = rc->mbtree.srcdim[1];
519 for( int y = 0; y < height; y++, input += stride, output += h->mb.i_mb_width )
520 {
521 float *coeff = rc->mbtree.coeffs[0];
522 for( int x = 0; x < h->mb.i_mb_width; x++, coeff+=filtersize )
523 output[x] = tapfilter( input, rc->mbtree.pos[0][x], stride, 1, coeff, filtersize );
524 }
525
526 /* V scale next */
527 input = rc->mbtree.scale_buffer[1];
528 output = dst;
529 filtersize = rc->mbtree.filtersize[1];
530 stride = h->mb.i_mb_width;
531 height = rc->mbtree.srcdim[1];
532 for( int x = 0; x < h->mb.i_mb_width; x++, input++, output++ )
533 {
534 float *coeff = rc->mbtree.coeffs[1];
535 for( int y = 0; y < h->mb.i_mb_height; y++, coeff+=filtersize )
536 output[y*stride] = tapfilter( input, rc->mbtree.pos[1][y], height, stride, coeff, filtersize );
537 }
538}

540int x264_macroblock_tree_read( x264_t *h, x264_frame_t *frame, float *quant_offsets )
541{
542 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
543 uint8_t i_type_actual = rc->entry[frame->i_frame].pict_type;
544
545 if( rc->entry[frame->i_frame].kept_as_ref )
546 {
547 uint8_t i_type;
548 if( rc->mbtree.qpbuf_pos < 0 )
549 {
550 do
551 {
552 rc->mbtree.qpbuf_pos++;
553
554 if( !fread( &i_type, 1, 1, rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_in ) )
555 goto fail;
556 if( fread( rc->mbtree.qp_buffer[rc->mbtree.qpbuf_pos], sizeof(uint16_t), rc->mbtree.src_mb_count, rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_in ) != (unsigned)rc->mbtree.src_mb_count )
557 goto fail;
558
559 if( i_type != i_type_actual && rc->mbtree.qpbuf_pos == 1 )
560 {
561 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "MB-tree frametype %d doesn't match actual frametype %d.\n", i_type, i_type_actual );
562 return -1;
563 }
564 } while( i_type != i_type_actual );
565 }
566
567 float *dst = rc->mbtree.rescale_enabled ? rc->mbtree.scale_buffer[0] : frame->f_qp_offset;
568 h->mc.mbtree_fix8_unpack( dst, rc->mbtree.qp_buffer[rc->mbtree.qpbuf_pos], rc->mbtree.src_mb_count );
569 if( rc->mbtree.rescale_enabled )
570 macroblock_tree_rescale( h, rc, frame->f_qp_offset );
571 if( h->frames.b_have_lowres )
572 for( int i = 0; i < h->mb.i_mb_count; i++ )
573 frame->i_inv_qscale_factor[i] = x264_exp2fix8( frame->f_qp_offset[i] );
574 rc->mbtree.qpbuf_pos--;
575 }
576 else
577 x264_adaptive_quant_frame( h, frame, quant_offsets );
578 return 0;
579fail:
580 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "Incomplete MB-tree stats file.\n" );
581 return -1;
582}
583
584int x264_reference_build_list_optimal( x264_t *h )
585{
586 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = h->rc->rce;
587 x264_frame_t *frames[16];
588 x264_weight_t weights[16][3];
589 int refcount[16];
590
591 if( rce->refs != h->i_ref[0] )
592 return -1;
593
594 memcpy( frames, h->fref[0], sizeof(frames) );
595 memcpy( refcount, rce->refcount, sizeof(refcount) );
596 memcpy( weights, h->fenc->weight, sizeof(weights) );
597 memset( &h->fenc->weight[1][0], 0, sizeof(x264_weight_t[15][3]) );
598
599 /* For now don't reorder ref 0; it seems to lower quality
600 in most cases due to skips. */
601 for( int ref = 1; ref < h->i_ref[0]; ref++ )
602 {
603 int max = -1;
604 int bestref = 1;
605
606 for( int i = 1; i < h->i_ref[0]; i++ )
607 /* Favor lower POC as a tiebreaker. */
608 COPY2_IF_GT( max, refcount[i], bestref, i );
609
610 /* FIXME: If there are duplicates from frames other than ref0 then it is possible
611 * that the optimal ordering doesnt place every duplicate. */
612
613 refcount[bestref] = -1;
614 h->fref[0][ref] = frames[bestref];
615 memcpy( h->fenc->weight[ref], weights[bestref], sizeof(weights[bestref]) );
616 }
617
618 return 0;
619}
620
621static char *strcat_filename( char *input, char *suffix )
622{
623 char *output = x264_malloc( strlen( input ) + strlen( suffix ) + 1 );
624 if( !output )
625 return NULL;
626 strcpy( output, input );
627 strcat( output, suffix );
628 return output;
629}
630
631void x264_ratecontrol_init_reconfigurable( x264_t *h, int b_init )
632{
633 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
634 if( !b_init && rc->b_2pass )
635 return;
636
637 if( h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_CRF )
638 {
639 /* Arbitrary rescaling to make CRF somewhat similar to QP.
640 * Try to compensate for MB-tree's effects as well. */
641 double base_cplx = h->mb.i_mb_count * (h->param.i_bframe ? 120 : 80);
642 double mbtree_offset = h->param.rc.b_mb_tree ? (1.0-h->param.rc.f_qcompress)*13.5 : 0;
643 rc->rate_factor_constant = pow( base_cplx, 1 - rc->qcompress )
644 / qp2qscale( h->param.rc.f_rf_constant + mbtree_offset + QP_BD_OFFSET );
645 }
646
647 if( h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate > 0 && h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size > 0 )
648 {
649 /* We don't support changing the ABR bitrate right now,
650 so if the stream starts as CBR, keep it CBR. */
651 if( rc->b_vbv_min_rate )
652 h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate = h->param.rc.i_bitrate;
653
654 if( h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size < (int)(h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate / rc->fps) )
655 {
656 h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size = h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate / rc->fps;
657 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "VBV buffer size cannot be smaller than one frame, using %d kbit\n",
658 h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size );
659 }
660
661 int kilobit_size = h->param.i_avcintra_class ? 1024 : 1000;
662 int vbv_buffer_size = h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size * kilobit_size;
663 int vbv_max_bitrate = h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate * kilobit_size;
664
665 /* Init HRD */
666 if( h->param.i_nal_hrd && b_init )
667 {
668 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_cnt = 1;
669 h->sps->vui.hrd.b_cbr_hrd = h->param.i_nal_hrd == X264_NAL_HRD_CBR;
670 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_time_offset_length = 0;
671
672 #define BR_SHIFT 6
673 #define CPB_SHIFT 4
674
675 // normalize HRD size and rate to the value / scale notation
676 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_scale = x264_clip3( x264_ctz( vbv_max_bitrate ) - BR_SHIFT, 0, 15 );
677 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_value = vbv_max_bitrate >> ( h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_scale + BR_SHIFT );
678 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled = h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_value << ( h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_scale + BR_SHIFT );
679 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_scale = x264_clip3( x264_ctz( vbv_buffer_size ) - CPB_SHIFT, 0, 15 );
680 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_value = vbv_buffer_size >> ( h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_scale + CPB_SHIFT );
681 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_unscaled = h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_value << ( h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_scale + CPB_SHIFT );
682
683 #undef CPB_SHIFT
684 #undef BR_SHIFT
685
686 // arbitrary
687 #define MAX_DURATION 0.5
688
689 int max_cpb_output_delay = X264_MIN( h->param.i_keyint_max * MAX_DURATION * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale / h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick, INT_MAX );
690 int max_dpb_output_delay = h->sps->vui.i_max_dec_frame_buffering * MAX_DURATION * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale / h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick;
691 int max_delay = (int)(90000.0 * (double)h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_unscaled / h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled + 0.5);
692
693 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_initial_cpb_removal_delay_length = 2 + x264_clip3( 32 - x264_clz( max_delay ), 4, 22 );
694 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_removal_delay_length = x264_clip3( 32 - x264_clz( max_cpb_output_delay ), 4, 31 );
695 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_dpb_output_delay_length = x264_clip3( 32 - x264_clz( max_dpb_output_delay ), 4, 31 );
696
697 #undef MAX_DURATION
698
699 vbv_buffer_size = h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_unscaled;
700 vbv_max_bitrate = h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled;
701 }
702 else if( h->param.i_nal_hrd && !b_init )
703 {
704 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "VBV parameters cannot be changed when NAL HRD is in use\n" );
705 return;
706 }
707 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled = vbv_max_bitrate;
708 h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_unscaled = vbv_buffer_size;
709
710 if( rc->b_vbv_min_rate )
711 rc->bitrate = (double)h->param.rc.i_bitrate * kilobit_size;
712 rc->buffer_rate = vbv_max_bitrate / rc->fps;
713 rc->vbv_max_rate = vbv_max_bitrate;
714 rc->buffer_size = vbv_buffer_size;
715 rc->single_frame_vbv = rc->buffer_rate * 1.1 > rc->buffer_size;
716 if( rc->b_abr && h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_ABR )
717 rc->cbr_decay = 1.0 - rc->buffer_rate / rc->buffer_size
718 * 0.5 * X264_MAX(0, 1.5 - rc->buffer_rate * rc->fps / rc->bitrate);
719 if( h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_CRF && h->param.rc.f_rf_constant_max )
720 {
721 rc->rate_factor_max_increment = h->param.rc.f_rf_constant_max - h->param.rc.f_rf_constant;
722 if( rc->rate_factor_max_increment <= 0 )
723 {
724 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "CRF max must be greater than CRF\n" );
725 rc->rate_factor_max_increment = 0;
726 }
727 }
728 if( b_init )
729 {
730 if( h->param.rc.f_vbv_buffer_init > 1. )
731 h->param.rc.f_vbv_buffer_init = x264_clip3f( h->param.rc.f_vbv_buffer_init / h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size, 0, 1 );
732 h->param.rc.f_vbv_buffer_init = x264_clip3f( X264_MAX( h->param.rc.f_vbv_buffer_init, rc->buffer_rate / rc->buffer_size ), 0, 1);
733 rc->buffer_fill_final =
734 rc->buffer_fill_final_min = rc->buffer_size * h->param.rc.f_vbv_buffer_init * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
735 rc->b_vbv = 1;
736 rc->b_vbv_min_rate = !rc->b_2pass
737 && h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_ABR
738 && h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate <= h->param.rc.i_bitrate;
739 }
740 }
741}
742
743int x264_ratecontrol_new( x264_t *h )
744{
745 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc;
746
747 x264_emms();
748
749 CHECKED_MALLOCZERO( h->rc, h->param.i_threads * sizeof(x264_ratecontrol_t) );
750 rc = h->rc;
751
752 rc->b_abr = h->param.rc.i_rc_method != X264_RC_CQP && !h->param.rc.b_stat_read;
753 rc->b_2pass = h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_ABR && h->param.rc.b_stat_read;
754
755 /* FIXME: use integers */
756 if( h->param.i_fps_num > 0 && h->param.i_fps_den > 0 )
757 rc->fps = (float) h->param.i_fps_num / h->param.i_fps_den;
758 else
759 rc->fps = 25.0;
760
761 if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree )
762 {
763 h->param.rc.f_pb_factor = 1;
764 rc->qcompress = 1;
765 }
766 else
767 rc->qcompress = h->param.rc.f_qcompress;
768
769 rc->bitrate = h->param.rc.i_bitrate * (h->param.i_avcintra_class ? 1024. : 1000.);
770 rc->rate_tolerance = h->param.rc.f_rate_tolerance;
771 rc->nmb = h->mb.i_mb_count;
772 rc->last_non_b_pict_type = -1;
773 rc->cbr_decay = 1.0;
774
775 if( h->param.rc.i_rc_method != X264_RC_ABR && h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
776 {
777 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "CRF/CQP is incompatible with 2pass.\n" );
778 return -1;
779 }
780
781 x264_ratecontrol_init_reconfigurable( h, 1 );
782
783 if( h->param.i_nal_hrd )
784 {
785 uint64_t denom = (uint64_t)h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
786 uint64_t num = 90000;
787 x264_reduce_fraction64( &num, &denom );
788 rc->hrd_multiply_denom = 90000 / num;
789
790 double bits_required = log2( num )
791 + log2( h->sps->vui.i_time_scale )
792 + log2( h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_unscaled );
793 if( bits_required >= 63 )
794 {
795 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "HRD with very large timescale and bufsize not supported\n" );
796 return -1;
797 }
798 }
799
800 if( rc->rate_tolerance < 0.01 )
801 {
802 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "bitrate tolerance too small, using .01\n" );
803 rc->rate_tolerance = 0.01;
804 }
805
806 h->mb.b_variable_qp = rc->b_vbv || h->param.rc.i_aq_mode;
807
808 if( rc->b_abr )
809 {
810 /* FIXME ABR_INIT_QP is actually used only in CRF */
811#define ABR_INIT_QP (( h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_CRF ? h->param.rc.f_rf_constant : 24 ) + QP_BD_OFFSET)
812 rc->accum_p_norm = .01;
813 rc->accum_p_qp = ABR_INIT_QP * rc->accum_p_norm;
814 /* estimated ratio that produces a reasonable QP for the first I-frame */
815 rc->cplxr_sum = .01 * pow( 7.0e5, rc->qcompress ) * pow( h->mb.i_mb_count, 0.5 );
816 rc->wanted_bits_window = 1.0 * rc->bitrate / rc->fps;
817 rc->last_non_b_pict_type = SLICE_TYPE_I;
818 }
819
820 rc->ip_offset = 6.0 * log2f( h->param.rc.f_ip_factor );
821 rc->pb_offset = 6.0 * log2f( h->param.rc.f_pb_factor );
822 rc->qp_constant[SLICE_TYPE_P] = h->param.rc.i_qp_constant;
823 rc->qp_constant[SLICE_TYPE_I] = x264_clip3( h->param.rc.i_qp_constant - rc->ip_offset + 0.5, 0, QP_MAX );
824 rc->qp_constant[SLICE_TYPE_B] = x264_clip3( h->param.rc.i_qp_constant + rc->pb_offset + 0.5, 0, QP_MAX );
825 h->mb.ip_offset = rc->ip_offset + 0.5;
826
827 rc->lstep = pow( 2, h->param.rc.i_qp_step / 6.0 );
828 rc->last_qscale = qp2qscale( 26 + QP_BD_OFFSET );
829 int num_preds = h->param.b_sliced_threads * h->param.i_threads + 1;
830 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->pred, 5 * sizeof(predictor_t) * num_preds );
831 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->pred_b_from_p, sizeof(predictor_t) );
832 static const float pred_coeff_table[3] = { 1.0, 1.0, 1.5 };
833 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
834 {
835 rc->last_qscale_for[i] = qp2qscale( ABR_INIT_QP );
836 rc->lmin[i] = qp2qscale( h->param.rc.i_qp_min );
837 rc->lmax[i] = qp2qscale( h->param.rc.i_qp_max );
838 for( int j = 0; j < num_preds; j++ )
839 {
840 rc->pred[i+j*5].coeff_min = pred_coeff_table[i] / 2;
841 rc->pred[i+j*5].coeff = pred_coeff_table[i];
842 rc->pred[i+j*5].count = 1.0;
843 rc->pred[i+j*5].decay = 0.5;
844 rc->pred[i+j*5].offset = 0.0;
845 }
846 for( int j = 0; j < 2; j++ )
847 {
848 rc->row_preds[i][j].coeff_min = .25 / 4;
849 rc->row_preds[i][j].coeff = .25;
850 rc->row_preds[i][j].count = 1.0;
851 rc->row_preds[i][j].decay = 0.5;
852 rc->row_preds[i][j].offset = 0.0;
853 }
854 }
855 rc->pred_b_from_p->coeff_min = 0.5 / 2;
856 rc->pred_b_from_p->coeff = 0.5;
857 rc->pred_b_from_p->count = 1.0;
858 rc->pred_b_from_p->decay = 0.5;
859 rc->pred_b_from_p->offset = 0.0;
860
861 if( parse_zones( h ) < 0 )
862 {
863 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "failed to parse zones\n" );
864 return -1;
865 }
866
867 /* Load stat file and init 2pass algo */
868 if( h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
869 {
870 char *p, *stats_in, *stats_buf;
871
872 /* read 1st pass stats */
873 assert( h->param.rc.psz_stat_in );
874 stats_buf = stats_in = x264_slurp_file( h->param.rc.psz_stat_in );
875 if( !stats_buf )
876 {
877 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "ratecontrol_init: can't open stats file\n" );
878 return -1;
879 }
880 if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree )
881 {
882 char *mbtree_stats_in = strcat_filename( h->param.rc.psz_stat_in, ".mbtree" );
883 if( !mbtree_stats_in )
884 return -1;
885 rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_in = x264_fopen( mbtree_stats_in, "rb" );
886 x264_free( mbtree_stats_in );
887 if( !rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_in )
888 {
889 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "ratecontrol_init: can't open mbtree stats file\n" );
890 return -1;
891 }
892 }
893
894 /* check whether 1st pass options were compatible with current options */
895 if( strncmp( stats_buf, "#options:", 9 ) )
896 {
897 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "options list in stats file not valid\n" );
898 return -1;
899 }
900
901 float res_factor, res_factor_bits;
902 {
903 int i, j;
904 uint32_t k, l;
905 char *opts = stats_buf;
906 stats_in = strchr( stats_buf, '\n' );
907 if( !stats_in )
908 return -1;
909 *stats_in = '\0';
910 stats_in++;
911 if( sscanf( opts, "#options: %dx%d", &i, &j ) != 2 )
912 {
913 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "resolution specified in stats file not valid\n" );
914 return -1;
915 }
916 else if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree )
917 {
918 rc->mbtree.srcdim[0] = i;
919 rc->mbtree.srcdim[1] = j;
920 }
921 res_factor = (float)h->param.i_width * h->param.i_height / (i*j);
922 /* Change in bits relative to resolution isn't quite linear on typical sources,
923 * so we'll at least try to roughly approximate this effect. */
924 res_factor_bits = powf( res_factor, 0.7 );
925
926 if( !( p = strstr( opts, "timebase=" ) ) || sscanf( p, "timebase=%u/%u", &k, &l ) != 2 )
927 {
928 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "timebase specified in stats file not valid\n" );
929 return -1;
930 }
931 if( k != h->param.i_timebase_num || l != h->param.i_timebase_den )
932 {
933 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "timebase mismatch with 1st pass (%u/%u vs %u/%u)\n",
934 h->param.i_timebase_num, h->param.i_timebase_den, k, l );
935 return -1;
936 }
937
938 CMP_OPT_FIRST_PASS( "bitdepth", BIT_DEPTH );
939 CMP_OPT_FIRST_PASS( "weightp", X264_MAX( 0, h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred ) );
940 CMP_OPT_FIRST_PASS( "bframes", h->param.i_bframe );
941 CMP_OPT_FIRST_PASS( "b_pyramid", h->param.i_bframe_pyramid );
942 CMP_OPT_FIRST_PASS( "intra_refresh", h->param.b_intra_refresh );
943 CMP_OPT_FIRST_PASS( "open_gop", h->param.b_open_gop );
944 CMP_OPT_FIRST_PASS( "bluray_compat", h->param.b_bluray_compat );
945 CMP_OPT_FIRST_PASS( "mbtree", h->param.rc.b_mb_tree );
946
947 if( (p = strstr( opts, "interlaced=" )) )
948 {
949 char *current = h->param.b_interlaced ? h->param.b_tff ? "tff" : "bff" : h->param.b_fake_interlaced ? "fake" : "0";
950 char buf[5];
951 sscanf( p, "interlaced=%4s", buf );
952 if( strcmp( current, buf ) )
953 {
954 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "different interlaced setting than first pass (%s vs %s)\n", current, buf );
955 return -1;
956 }
957 }
958
959 if( (p = strstr( opts, "keyint=" )) )
960 {
961 p += 7;
962 char buf[13] = "infinite ";
963 if( h->param.i_keyint_max != X264_KEYINT_MAX_INFINITE )
964 sprintf( buf, "%d ", h->param.i_keyint_max );
965 if( strncmp( p, buf, strlen(buf) ) )
966 {
967 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "different keyint setting than first pass (%.*s vs %.*s)\n",
968 strlen(buf)-1, buf, strcspn(p, " "), p );
969 return -1;
970 }
971 }
972
973 if( strstr( opts, "qp=0" ) && h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_ABR )
974 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "1st pass was lossless, bitrate prediction will be inaccurate\n" );
975
976 if( !strstr( opts, "direct=3" ) && h->param.analyse.i_direct_mv_pred == X264_DIRECT_PRED_AUTO )
977 {
978 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "direct=auto not used on the first pass\n" );
979 h->mb.b_direct_auto_write = 1;
980 }
981
982 if( ( p = strstr( opts, "b_adapt=" ) ) && sscanf( p, "b_adapt=%d", &i ) && i >= X264_B_ADAPT_NONE && i <= X264_B_ADAPT_TRELLIS )
983 h->param.i_bframe_adaptive = i;
984 else if( h->param.i_bframe )
985 {
986 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "b_adapt method specified in stats file not valid\n" );
987 return -1;
988 }
989
990 if( (h->param.rc.b_mb_tree || h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size) && ( p = strstr( opts, "rc_lookahead=" ) ) && sscanf( p, "rc_lookahead=%d", &i ) )
991 h->param.rc.i_lookahead = i;
992 }
993
994 /* find number of pics */
995 p = stats_in;
996 int num_entries;
997 for( num_entries = -1; p; num_entries++ )
998 p = strchr( p + 1, ';' );
999 if( !num_entries )
1000 {
1001 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "empty stats file\n" );
1002 return -1;
1003 }
1004 rc->num_entries = num_entries;
1005
1006 if( h->param.i_frame_total < rc->num_entries && h->param.i_frame_total > 0 )
1007 {
1008 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "2nd pass has fewer frames than 1st pass (%d vs %d)\n",
1009 h->param.i_frame_total, rc->num_entries );
1010 }
1011 if( h->param.i_frame_total > rc->num_entries )
1012 {
1013 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "2nd pass has more frames than 1st pass (%d vs %d)\n",
1014 h->param.i_frame_total, rc->num_entries );
1015 return -1;
1016 }
1017
1018 CHECKED_MALLOCZERO( rc->entry, rc->num_entries * sizeof(ratecontrol_entry_t) );
1019 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->entry_out, rc->num_entries * sizeof(ratecontrol_entry_t*) );
1020
1021 /* init all to skipped p frames */
1022 for( int i = 0; i < rc->num_entries; i++ )
1023 {
1024 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = &rc->entry[i];
1025 rce->pict_type = SLICE_TYPE_P;
1026 rce->qscale = rce->new_qscale = qp2qscale( 20 + QP_BD_OFFSET );
1027 rce->misc_bits = rc->nmb + 10;
1028 rce->new_qp = 0;
1029 rc->entry_out[i] = rce;
1030 }
1031
1032 /* read stats */
1033 p = stats_in;
1034 double total_qp_aq = 0;
1035 for( int i = 0; i < rc->num_entries; i++ )
1036 {
1037 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce;
1038 int frame_number = 0;
1039 int frame_out_number = 0;
1040 char pict_type = 0;
1041 int e;
1042 char *next;
1043 float qp_rc, qp_aq;
1044 int ref;
1045
1046 next= strchr(p, ';');
1047 if( next )
1048 *next++ = 0; //sscanf is unbelievably slow on long strings
1049 e = sscanf( p, " in:%d out:%d ", &frame_number, &frame_out_number );
1050
1051 if( frame_number < 0 || frame_number >= rc->num_entries )
1052 {
1053 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "bad frame number (%d) at stats line %d\n", frame_number, i );
1054 return -1;
1055 }
1056 if( frame_out_number < 0 || frame_out_number >= rc->num_entries )
1057 {
1058 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "bad frame output number (%d) at stats line %d\n", frame_out_number, i );
1059 return -1;
1060 }
1061 rce = &rc->entry[frame_number];
1062 rc->entry_out[frame_out_number] = rce;
1063 rce->direct_mode = 0;
1064
1065 e += sscanf( p, " in:%*d out:%*d type:%c dur:%"SCNd64" cpbdur:%"SCNd64" q:%f aq:%f tex:%d mv:%d misc:%d imb:%d pmb:%d smb:%d d:%c",
1066 &pict_type, &rce->i_duration, &rce->i_cpb_duration, &qp_rc, &qp_aq, &rce->tex_bits,
1067 &rce->mv_bits, &rce->misc_bits, &rce->i_count, &rce->p_count,
1068 &rce->s_count, &rce->direct_mode );
1069 rce->tex_bits *= res_factor_bits;
1070 rce->mv_bits *= res_factor_bits;
1071 rce->misc_bits *= res_factor_bits;
1072 rce->i_count *= res_factor;
1073 rce->p_count *= res_factor;
1074 rce->s_count *= res_factor;
1075
1076 p = strstr( p, "ref:" );
1077 if( !p )
1078 goto parse_error;
1079 p += 4;
1080 for( ref = 0; ref < 16; ref++ )
1081 {
1082 if( sscanf( p, " %d", &rce->refcount[ref] ) != 1 )
1083 break;
1084 p = strchr( p+1, ' ' );
1085 if( !p )
1086 goto parse_error;
1087 }
1088 rce->refs = ref;
1089
1090 /* find weights */
1091 rce->i_weight_denom[0] = rce->i_weight_denom[1] = -1;
1092 char *w = strchr( p, 'w' );
1093 if( w )
1094 {
1095 int count = sscanf( w, "w:%hd,%hd,%hd,%hd,%hd,%hd,%hd,%hd",
1096 &rce->i_weight_denom[0], &rce->weight[0][0], &rce->weight[0][1],
1097 &rce->i_weight_denom[1], &rce->weight[1][0], &rce->weight[1][1],
1098 &rce->weight[2][0], &rce->weight[2][1] );
1099 if( count == 3 )
1100 rce->i_weight_denom[1] = -1;
1101 else if( count != 8 )
1102 rce->i_weight_denom[0] = rce->i_weight_denom[1] = -1;
1103 }
1104
1105 if( pict_type != 'b' )
1106 rce->kept_as_ref = 1;
1107 switch( pict_type )
1108 {
1109 case 'I':
1110 rce->frame_type = X264_TYPE_IDR;
1111 rce->pict_type = SLICE_TYPE_I;
1112 break;
1113 case 'i':
1114 rce->frame_type = X264_TYPE_I;
1115 rce->pict_type = SLICE_TYPE_I;
1116 break;
1117 case 'P':
1118 rce->frame_type = X264_TYPE_P;
1119 rce->pict_type = SLICE_TYPE_P;
1120 break;
1121 case 'B':
1122 rce->frame_type = X264_TYPE_BREF;
1123 rce->pict_type = SLICE_TYPE_B;
1124 break;
1125 case 'b':
1126 rce->frame_type = X264_TYPE_B;
1127 rce->pict_type = SLICE_TYPE_B;
1128 break;
1129 default: e = -1; break;
1130 }
1131 if( e < 14 )
1132 {
1133parse_error:
1134 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "statistics are damaged at line %d, parser out=%d\n", i, e );
1135 return -1;
1136 }
1137 rce->qscale = qp2qscale( qp_rc );
1138 total_qp_aq += qp_aq;
1139 p = next;
1140 }
1141 if( !h->param.b_stitchable )
1142 h->pps->i_pic_init_qp = SPEC_QP( (int)(total_qp_aq / rc->num_entries + 0.5) );
1143
1144 x264_free( stats_buf );
1145
1146 if( h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_ABR )
1147 {
1148 if( init_pass2( h ) < 0 )
1149 return -1;
1150 } /* else we're using constant quant, so no need to run the bitrate allocation */
1151 }
1152
1153 /* Open output file */
1154 /* If input and output files are the same, output to a temp file
1155 * and move it to the real name only when it's complete */
1156 if( h->param.rc.b_stat_write )
1157 {
1158 char *p;
1159 rc->psz_stat_file_tmpname = strcat_filename( h->param.rc.psz_stat_out, ".temp" );
1160 if( !rc->psz_stat_file_tmpname )
1161 return -1;
1162
1163 rc->p_stat_file_out = x264_fopen( rc->psz_stat_file_tmpname, "wb" );
1164 if( rc->p_stat_file_out == NULL )
1165 {
1166 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "ratecontrol_init: can't open stats file\n" );
1167 return -1;
1168 }
1169
1170 p = x264_param2string( &h->param, 1 );
1171 if( p )
1172 fprintf( rc->p_stat_file_out, "#options: %s\n", p );
1173 x264_free( p );
1174 if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree && !h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
1175 {
1176 rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_tmpname = strcat_filename( h->param.rc.psz_stat_out, ".mbtree.temp" );
1177 rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_name = strcat_filename( h->param.rc.psz_stat_out, ".mbtree" );
1178 if( !rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_tmpname || !rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_name )
1179 return -1;
1180
1181 rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_out = x264_fopen( rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_tmpname, "wb" );
1182 if( rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_out == NULL )
1183 {
1184 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "ratecontrol_init: can't open mbtree stats file\n" );
1185 return -1;
1186 }
1187 }
1188 }
1189
1190 if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree && (h->param.rc.b_stat_read || h->param.rc.b_stat_write) )
1191 {
1192 if( !h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
1193 {
1194 rc->mbtree.srcdim[0] = h->param.i_width;
1195 rc->mbtree.srcdim[1] = h->param.i_height;
1196 }
1197 if( macroblock_tree_rescale_init( h, rc ) < 0 )
1198 return -1;
1199 }
1200
1201 for( int i = 0; i<h->param.i_threads; i++ )
1202 {
1203 h->thread[i]->rc = rc+i;
1204 if( i )
1205 {
1206 rc[i] = rc[0];
1207 h->thread[i]->param = h->param;
1208 h->thread[i]->mb.b_variable_qp = h->mb.b_variable_qp;
1209 h->thread[i]->mb.ip_offset = h->mb.ip_offset;
1210 }
1211 }
1212
1213 return 0;
1214fail:
1215 return -1;
1216}
1217
1218static int parse_zone( x264_t *h, x264_zone_t *z, char *p )
1219{
1220 int len = 0;
1221 char *tok, UNUSED *saveptr=NULL;
1222 z->param = NULL;
1223 z->f_bitrate_factor = 1;
1224 if( 3 <= sscanf(p, "%d,%d,q=%d%n", &z->i_start, &z->i_end, &z->i_qp, &len) )
1225 z->b_force_qp = 1;
1226 else if( 3 <= sscanf(p, "%d,%d,b=%f%n", &z->i_start, &z->i_end, &z->f_bitrate_factor, &len) )
1227 z->b_force_qp = 0;
1228 else if( 2 <= sscanf(p, "%d,%d%n", &z->i_start, &z->i_end, &len) )
1229 z->b_force_qp = 0;
1230 else
1231 {
1232 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "invalid zone: \"%s\"\n", p );
1233 return -1;
1234 }
1235 p += len;
1236 if( !*p )
1237 return 0;
1238 CHECKED_MALLOC( z->param, sizeof(x264_param_t) );
1239 memcpy( z->param, &h->param, sizeof(x264_param_t) );
1240 z->param->opaque = NULL;
1241 z->param->param_free = x264_free;
1242 while( (tok = strtok_r( p, ",", &saveptr )) )
1243 {
1244 char *val = strchr( tok, '=' );
1245 if( val )
1246 {
1247 *val = '\0';
1248 val++;
1249 }
1250 if( x264_param_parse( z->param, tok, val ) )
1251 {
1252 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "invalid zone param: %s = %s\n", tok, val );
1253 return -1;
1254 }
1255 p = NULL;
1256 }
1257 return 0;
1258fail:
1259 return -1;
1260}
1261
1262static int parse_zones( x264_t *h )
1263{
1264 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1265 if( h->param.rc.psz_zones && !h->param.rc.i_zones )
1266 {
1267 char *psz_zones, *p;
1268 CHECKED_MALLOC( psz_zones, strlen( h->param.rc.psz_zones )+1 );
1269 strcpy( psz_zones, h->param.rc.psz_zones );
1270 h->param.rc.i_zones = 1;
1271 for( p = psz_zones; *p; p++ )
1272 h->param.rc.i_zones += (*p == '/');
1273 CHECKED_MALLOC( h->param.rc.zones, h->param.rc.i_zones * sizeof(x264_zone_t) );
1274 p = psz_zones;
1275 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.rc.i_zones; i++ )
1276 {
1277 int i_tok = strcspn( p, "/" );
1278 p[i_tok] = 0;
1279 if( parse_zone( h, &h->param.rc.zones[i], p ) )
1280 {
1281 x264_free( psz_zones );
1282 return -1;
1283 }
1284 p += i_tok + 1;
1285 }
1286 x264_free( psz_zones );
1287 }
1288
1289 if( h->param.rc.i_zones > 0 )
1290 {
1291 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.rc.i_zones; i++ )
1292 {
1293 x264_zone_t z = h->param.rc.zones[i];
1294 if( z.i_start < 0 || z.i_start > z.i_end )
1295 {
1296 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "invalid zone: start=%d end=%d\n",
1297 z.i_start, z.i_end );
1298 return -1;
1299 }
1300 else if( !z.b_force_qp && z.f_bitrate_factor <= 0 )
1301 {
1302 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "invalid zone: bitrate_factor=%f\n",
1303 z.f_bitrate_factor );
1304 return -1;
1305 }
1306 }
1307
1308 rc->i_zones = h->param.rc.i_zones + 1;
1309 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->zones, rc->i_zones * sizeof(x264_zone_t) );
1310 memcpy( rc->zones+1, h->param.rc.zones, (rc->i_zones-1) * sizeof(x264_zone_t) );
1311
1312 // default zone to fall back to if none of the others match
1313 rc->zones[0].i_start = 0;
1314 rc->zones[0].i_end = INT_MAX;
1315 rc->zones[0].b_force_qp = 0;
1316 rc->zones[0].f_bitrate_factor = 1;
1317 CHECKED_MALLOC( rc->zones[0].param, sizeof(x264_param_t) );
1318 memcpy( rc->zones[0].param, &h->param, sizeof(x264_param_t) );
1319 rc->zones[0].param->opaque = NULL;
1320 for( int i = 1; i < rc->i_zones; i++ )
1321 {
1322 if( !rc->zones[i].param )
1323 rc->zones[i].param = rc->zones[0].param;
1324 }
1325 }
1326
1327 return 0;
1328fail:
1329 return -1;
1330}
1331
1332static x264_zone_t *get_zone( x264_t *h, int frame_num )
1333{
1334 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1335 for( int i = rc->i_zones - 1; i >= 0; i-- )
1336 {
1337 x264_zone_t *z = &rc->zones[i];
1338 if( frame_num >= z->i_start && frame_num <= z->i_end )
1339 return z;
1340 }
1341 return NULL;
1342}
1343
1344void x264_ratecontrol_summary( x264_t *h )
1345{
1346 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1347 if( rc->b_abr && h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_ABR && rc->cbr_decay > .9999 )
1348 {
1349 double base_cplx = h->mb.i_mb_count * (h->param.i_bframe ? 120 : 80);
1350 double mbtree_offset = h->param.rc.b_mb_tree ? (1.0-h->param.rc.f_qcompress)*13.5 : 0;
1351 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "final ratefactor: %.2f\n",
1352 qscale2qp( pow( base_cplx, 1 - rc->qcompress )
1353 * rc->cplxr_sum / rc->wanted_bits_window ) - mbtree_offset - QP_BD_OFFSET );
1354 }
1355}

1357void x264_ratecontrol_delete( x264_t *h )
1358{
1359 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1360 int b_regular_file;
1361
1362 if( rc->p_stat_file_out )
1363 {
1364 b_regular_file = x264_is_regular_file( rc->p_stat_file_out );
1365 fclose( rc->p_stat_file_out );
1366 if( h->i_frame >= rc->num_entries && b_regular_file )
1367 if( x264_rename( rc->psz_stat_file_tmpname, h->param.rc.psz_stat_out ) != 0 )
1368 {
1369 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "failed to rename \"%s\" to \"%s\"\n",
1370 rc->psz_stat_file_tmpname, h->param.rc.psz_stat_out );
1371 }
1372 x264_free( rc->psz_stat_file_tmpname );
1373 }
1374 if( rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_out )
1375 {
1376 b_regular_file = x264_is_regular_file( rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_out );
1377 fclose( rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_out );
1378 if( h->i_frame >= rc->num_entries && b_regular_file )
1379 if( x264_rename( rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_tmpname, rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_name ) != 0 )
1380 {
1381 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "failed to rename \"%s\" to \"%s\"\n",
1382 rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_tmpname, rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_name );
1383 }
1384 x264_free( rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_tmpname );
1385 x264_free( rc->psz_mbtree_stat_file_name );
1386 }
1387 if( rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_in )
1388 fclose( rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_in );
1389 x264_free( rc->pred );
1390 x264_free( rc->pred_b_from_p );
1391 x264_free( rc->entry );
1392 x264_free( rc->entry_out );
1393 macroblock_tree_rescale_destroy( rc );
1394 if( rc->zones )
1395 {
1396 x264_param_cleanup( rc->zones[0].param );
1397 x264_free( rc->zones[0].param );
1398 for( int i = 1; i < rc->i_zones; i++ )
1399 if( rc->zones[i].param != rc->zones[0].param && rc->zones[i].param->param_free )
1400 {
1401 x264_param_cleanup( rc->zones[i].param );
1402 rc->zones[i].param->param_free( rc->zones[i].param );
1403 }
1404 x264_free( rc->zones );
1405 }
1406 x264_free( rc );
1407}
1408
1409static void accum_p_qp_update( x264_t *h, float qp )
1410{
1411 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1412 rc->accum_p_qp *= .95;
1413 rc->accum_p_norm *= .95;
1414 rc->accum_p_norm += 1;
1415 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_I )
1416 rc->accum_p_qp += qp + rc->ip_offset;
1417 else
1418 rc->accum_p_qp += qp;
1419}
1420
1421void x264_ratecontrol_zone_init( x264_t *h )
1422{
1423 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1424 x264_zone_t *zone = get_zone( h, h->fenc->i_frame );
1425 if( zone && (!rc->prev_zone || zone->param != rc->prev_zone->param) )
1426 x264_encoder_reconfig_apply( h, zone->param );
1427 rc->prev_zone = zone;
1428}
1429
1430/* Before encoding a frame, choose a QP for it */
1431void x264_ratecontrol_start( x264_t *h, int i_force_qp, int overhead )
1432{
1433 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1434 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = NULL;
1435 x264_zone_t *zone = get_zone( h, h->fenc->i_frame );
1436 float q;
1437
1438 x264_emms();
1439
1440 if( h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
1441 {
1442 int frame = h->fenc->i_frame;
1443 assert( frame >= 0 && frame < rc->num_entries );
1444 rce = rc->rce = &rc->entry[frame];
1445
1446 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B
1447 && h->param.analyse.i_direct_mv_pred == X264_DIRECT_PRED_AUTO )
1448 {
1449 h->sh.b_direct_spatial_mv_pred = ( rce->direct_mode == 's' );
1450 h->mb.b_direct_auto_read = ( rce->direct_mode == 's' || rce->direct_mode == 't' );
1451 }
1452 }
1453
1454 if( rc->b_vbv )
1455 {
1456 memset( h->fdec->i_row_bits, 0, h->mb.i_mb_height * sizeof(int) );
1457 memset( h->fdec->f_row_qp, 0, h->mb.i_mb_height * sizeof(float) );
1458 memset( h->fdec->f_row_qscale, 0, h->mb.i_mb_height * sizeof(float) );
1459 rc->row_pred = rc->row_preds[h->sh.i_type];
1460 rc->buffer_rate = h->fenc->i_cpb_duration * rc->vbv_max_rate * h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
1461 update_vbv_plan( h, overhead );
1462
1463 const x264_level_t *l = x264_levels;
1464 while( l->level_idc != 0 && l->level_idc != h->param.i_level_idc )
1465 l++;
1466
1467 int mincr = l->mincr;
1468
1469 if( h->param.b_bluray_compat )
1470 mincr = 4;
1471
1472 /* Profiles above High don't require minCR, so just set the maximum to a large value. */
1473 if( h->sps->i_profile_idc > PROFILE_HIGH )
1474 rc->frame_size_maximum = 1e9;
1475 else
1476 {
1477 /* The spec has a bizarre special case for the first frame. */
1478 if( h->i_frame == 0 )
1479 {
1480 //384 * ( Max( PicSizeInMbs, fR * MaxMBPS ) + MaxMBPS * ( tr( 0 ) - tr,n( 0 ) ) ) / MinCR
1481 double fr = 1. / (h->param.i_level_idc >= 60 ? 300 : 172);
1482 int pic_size_in_mbs = h->mb.i_mb_width * h->mb.i_mb_height;
1483 rc->frame_size_maximum = 384 * BIT_DEPTH * X264_MAX( pic_size_in_mbs, fr*l->mbps ) / mincr;
1484 }
1485 else
1486 {
1487 //384 * MaxMBPS * ( tr( n ) - tr( n - 1 ) ) / MinCR
1488 rc->frame_size_maximum = 384 * BIT_DEPTH * ((double)h->fenc->i_cpb_duration * h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale) * l->mbps / mincr;
1489 }
1490 }
1491 }
1492
1493 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_B )
1494 rc->bframes = h->fenc->i_bframes;
1495
1496 if( rc->b_abr )
1497 {
1498 q = qscale2qp( rate_estimate_qscale( h ) );
1499 }
1500 else if( rc->b_2pass )
1501 {
1502 rce->new_qscale = rate_estimate_qscale( h );
1503 q = qscale2qp( rce->new_qscale );
1504 }
1505 else /* CQP */
1506 {
1507 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B && h->fdec->b_kept_as_ref )
1508 q = ( rc->qp_constant[ SLICE_TYPE_B ] + rc->qp_constant[ SLICE_TYPE_P ] ) / 2;
1509 else
1510 q = rc->qp_constant[ h->sh.i_type ];
1511
1512 if( zone )
1513 {
1514 if( zone->b_force_qp )
1515 q += zone->i_qp - rc->qp_constant[SLICE_TYPE_P];
1516 else
1517 q -= 6*log2f( zone->f_bitrate_factor );
1518 }
1519 }
1520 if( i_force_qp != X264_QP_AUTO )
1521 q = i_force_qp - 1;
1522
1523 q = x264_clip3f( q, h->param.rc.i_qp_min, h->param.rc.i_qp_max );
1524
1525 rc->qpa_rc = rc->qpa_rc_prev =
1526 rc->qpa_aq = rc->qpa_aq_prev = 0;
1527 h->fdec->f_qp_avg_rc =
1528 h->fdec->f_qp_avg_aq =
1529 rc->qpm = q;
1530 if( rce )
1531 rce->new_qp = q;
1532
1533 accum_p_qp_update( h, rc->qpm );
1534
1535 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_B )
1536 rc->last_non_b_pict_type = h->sh.i_type;
1537}
1538
1539static float predict_row_size( x264_t *h, int y, float qscale )
1540{
1541 /* average between two predictors:
1542 * absolute SATD, and scaled bit cost of the colocated row in the previous frame */
1543 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1544 float pred_s = predict_size( &rc->row_pred[0], qscale, h->fdec->i_row_satd[y] );
1545 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_I || qscale >= h->fref[0][0]->f_row_qscale[y] )
1546 {
1547 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_P
1548 && h->fref[0][0]->i_type == h->fdec->i_type
1549 && h->fref[0][0]->f_row_qscale[y] > 0
1550 && h->fref[0][0]->i_row_satd[y] > 0
1551 && (abs(h->fref[0][0]->i_row_satd[y] - h->fdec->i_row_satd[y]) < h->fdec->i_row_satd[y]/2))
1552 {
1553 float pred_t = h->fref[0][0]->i_row_bits[y] * h->fdec->i_row_satd[y] / h->fref[0][0]->i_row_satd[y]
1554 * h->fref[0][0]->f_row_qscale[y] / qscale;
1555 return (pred_s + pred_t) * 0.5f;
1556 }
1557 return pred_s;
1558 }
1559 /* Our QP is lower than the reference! */
1560 else
1561 {
1562 float pred_intra = predict_size( &rc->row_pred[1], qscale, h->fdec->i_row_satds[0][0][y] );
1563 /* Sum: better to overestimate than underestimate by using only one of the two predictors. */
1564 return pred_intra + pred_s;
1565 }
1566}
1567
1568static int row_bits_so_far( x264_t *h, int y )
1569{
1570 int bits = 0;
1571 for( int i = h->i_threadslice_start; i <= y; i++ )
1572 bits += h->fdec->i_row_bits[i];
1573 return bits;
1574}
1575
1576static float predict_row_size_to_end( x264_t *h, int y, float qp )
1577{
1578 float qscale = qp2qscale( qp );
1579 float bits = 0;
1580 for( int i = y+1; i < h->i_threadslice_end; i++ )
1581 bits += predict_row_size( h, i, qscale );
1582 return bits;
1583}
1584
1585/* TODO:
1586 * eliminate all use of qp in row ratecontrol: make it entirely qscale-based.
1587 * make this function stop being needlessly O(N^2)
1588 * update more often than once per row? */
1589int x264_ratecontrol_mb( x264_t *h, int bits )
1590{
1591 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1592 const int y = h->mb.i_mb_y;
1593
1594 h->fdec->i_row_bits[y] += bits;
1595 rc->qpa_aq += h->mb.i_qp;
1596
1597 if( h->mb.i_mb_x != h->mb.i_mb_width - 1 )
1598 return 0;
1599
1600 x264_emms();
1601 rc->qpa_rc += rc->qpm * h->mb.i_mb_width;
1602
1603 if( !rc->b_vbv )
1604 return 0;
1605
1606 float qscale = qp2qscale( rc->qpm );
1607 h->fdec->f_row_qp[y] = rc->qpm;
1608 h->fdec->f_row_qscale[y] = qscale;
1609
1610 update_predictor( &rc->row_pred[0], qscale, h->fdec->i_row_satd[y], h->fdec->i_row_bits[y] );
1611 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_I && rc->qpm < h->fref[0][0]->f_row_qp[y] )
1612 update_predictor( &rc->row_pred[1], qscale, h->fdec->i_row_satds[0][0][y], h->fdec->i_row_bits[y] );
1613
1614 /* update ratecontrol per-mbpair in MBAFF */
1615 if( SLICE_MBAFF && !(y&1) )
1616 return 0;
1617
1618 /* FIXME: We don't currently support the case where there's a slice
1619 * boundary in between. */
1620 int can_reencode_row = h->sh.i_first_mb <= ((h->mb.i_mb_y - SLICE_MBAFF) * h->mb.i_mb_stride);
1621
1622 /* tweak quality based on difference from predicted size */
1623 float prev_row_qp = h->fdec->f_row_qp[y];
1624 float qp_absolute_max = h->param.rc.i_qp_max;
1625 if( rc->rate_factor_max_increment )
1626 qp_absolute_max = X264_MIN( qp_absolute_max, rc->qp_novbv + rc->rate_factor_max_increment );
1627 float qp_max = X264_MIN( prev_row_qp + h->param.rc.i_qp_step, qp_absolute_max );
1628 float qp_min = X264_MAX( prev_row_qp - h->param.rc.i_qp_step, h->param.rc.i_qp_min );
1629 float step_size = 0.5f;
1630 float slice_size_planned = h->param.b_sliced_threads ? rc->slice_size_planned : rc->frame_size_planned;
1631 float bits_so_far = row_bits_so_far( h, y );
1632 float max_frame_error = x264_clip3f( 1.0 / h->mb.i_mb_height, 0.05, 0.25 );
1633 float max_frame_size = rc->frame_size_maximum - rc->frame_size_maximum * max_frame_error;
1634 max_frame_size = X264_MIN( max_frame_size, rc->buffer_fill - rc->buffer_rate * max_frame_error );
1635 float size_of_other_slices = 0;
1636 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
1637 {
1638 float size_of_other_slices_planned = 0;
1639 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
1640 if( h != h->thread[i] )
1641 {
1642 size_of_other_slices += h->thread[i]->rc->frame_size_estimated;
1643 size_of_other_slices_planned += h->thread[i]->rc->slice_size_planned;
1644 }
1645 float weight = rc->slice_size_planned / rc->frame_size_planned;
1646 size_of_other_slices = (size_of_other_slices - size_of_other_slices_planned) * weight + size_of_other_slices_planned;
1647 }
1648 if( y < h->i_threadslice_end-1 )
1649 {
1650 /* B-frames shouldn't use lower QP than their reference frames. */
1651 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
1652 {
1653 qp_min = X264_MAX( qp_min, X264_MAX( h->fref[0][0]->f_row_qp[y+1], h->fref[1][0]->f_row_qp[y+1] ) );
1654 rc->qpm = X264_MAX( rc->qpm, qp_min );
1655 }
1656
1657 float buffer_left_planned = rc->buffer_fill - rc->frame_size_planned;
1658 buffer_left_planned = X264_MAX( buffer_left_planned, 0.f );
1659 /* More threads means we have to be more cautious in letting ratecontrol use up extra bits. */
1660 float rc_tol = buffer_left_planned / h->param.i_threads * rc->rate_tolerance;
1661 float b1 = bits_so_far + predict_row_size_to_end( h, y, rc->qpm ) + size_of_other_slices;
1662 float trust_coeff = x264_clip3f( bits_so_far / slice_size_planned, 0.0, 1.0 );
1663
1664 /* Don't increase the row QPs until a sufficent amount of the bits of the frame have been processed, in case a flat */
1665 /* area at the top of the frame was measured inaccurately. */
1666 if( trust_coeff < 0.05f )
1667 qp_max = qp_absolute_max = prev_row_qp;
1668
1669 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_I )
1670 rc_tol *= 0.5f;
1671
1672 if( !rc->b_vbv_min_rate )
1673 qp_min = X264_MAX( qp_min, rc->qp_novbv );
1674
1675 while( rc->qpm < qp_max
1676 && ((b1 > rc->frame_size_planned + rc_tol) ||
1677 (b1 > rc->frame_size_planned && rc->qpm < rc->qp_novbv) ||
1678 (b1 > rc->buffer_fill - buffer_left_planned * 0.5f)) )
1679 {
1680 rc->qpm += step_size;
1681 b1 = bits_so_far + predict_row_size_to_end( h, y, rc->qpm ) + size_of_other_slices;
1682 }
1683
1684 float b_max = b1 + ((rc->buffer_fill - rc->buffer_size + rc->buffer_rate) * 0.90f - b1) * trust_coeff;
1685 rc->qpm -= step_size;
1686 float b2 = bits_so_far + predict_row_size_to_end( h, y, rc->qpm ) + size_of_other_slices;
1687 while( rc->qpm > qp_min && rc->qpm < prev_row_qp
1688 && (rc->qpm > h->fdec->f_row_qp[0] || rc->single_frame_vbv)
1689 && (b2 < max_frame_size)
1690 && ((b2 < rc->frame_size_planned * 0.8f) || (b2 < b_max)) )
1691 {
1692 b1 = b2;
1693 rc->qpm -= step_size;
1694 b2 = bits_so_far + predict_row_size_to_end( h, y, rc->qpm ) + size_of_other_slices;
1695 }
1696 rc->qpm += step_size;
1697
1698 /* avoid VBV underflow or MinCR violation */
1699 while( rc->qpm < qp_absolute_max && (b1 > max_frame_size) )
1700 {
1701 rc->qpm += step_size;
1702 b1 = bits_so_far + predict_row_size_to_end( h, y, rc->qpm ) + size_of_other_slices;
1703 }
1704
1705 rc->frame_size_estimated = b1 - size_of_other_slices;
1706
1707 /* If the current row was large enough to cause a large QP jump, try re-encoding it. */
1708 if( rc->qpm > qp_max && prev_row_qp < qp_max && can_reencode_row )
1709 {
1710 /* Bump QP to halfway in between... close enough. */
1711 rc->qpm = x264_clip3f( (prev_row_qp + rc->qpm)*0.5f, prev_row_qp + 1.0f, qp_max );
1712 rc->qpa_rc = rc->qpa_rc_prev;
1713 rc->qpa_aq = rc->qpa_aq_prev;
1714 h->fdec->i_row_bits[y] = 0;
1715 h->fdec->i_row_bits[y-SLICE_MBAFF] = 0;
1716 return -1;
1717 }
1718 }
1719 else
1720 {
1721 rc->frame_size_estimated = bits_so_far;
1722
1723 /* Last-ditch attempt: if the last row of the frame underflowed the VBV,
1724 * try again. */
1725 if( rc->qpm < qp_max && can_reencode_row
1726 && (bits_so_far + size_of_other_slices > X264_MIN( rc->frame_size_maximum, rc->buffer_fill )) )
1727 {
1728 rc->qpm = qp_max;
1729 rc->qpa_rc = rc->qpa_rc_prev;
1730 rc->qpa_aq = rc->qpa_aq_prev;
1731 h->fdec->i_row_bits[y] = 0;
1732 h->fdec->i_row_bits[y-SLICE_MBAFF] = 0;
1733 return -1;
1734 }
1735 }
1736
1737 rc->qpa_rc_prev = rc->qpa_rc;
1738 rc->qpa_aq_prev = rc->qpa_aq;
1739
1740 return 0;
1741}
1742
1743int x264_ratecontrol_qp( x264_t *h )
1744{
1745 x264_emms();
1746 return x264_clip3( h->rc->qpm + 0.5f, h->param.rc.i_qp_min, h->param.rc.i_qp_max );
1747}
1748
1749int x264_ratecontrol_mb_qp( x264_t *h )
1750{
1751 x264_emms();
1752 float qp = h->rc->qpm;
1753 if( h->param.rc.i_aq_mode )
1754 {
1755 /* MB-tree currently doesn't adjust quantizers in unreferenced frames. */
1756 float qp_offset = h->fdec->b_kept_as_ref ? h->fenc->f_qp_offset[h->mb.i_mb_xy] : h->fenc->f_qp_offset_aq[h->mb.i_mb_xy];
1757 /* Scale AQ's effect towards zero in emergency mode. */
1758 if( qp > QP_MAX_SPEC )
1759 qp_offset *= (QP_MAX - qp) / (QP_MAX - QP_MAX_SPEC);
1760 qp += qp_offset;
1761 }
1762 return x264_clip3( qp + 0.5f, h->param.rc.i_qp_min, h->param.rc.i_qp_max );
1763}
1764
1765/* In 2pass, force the same frame types as in the 1st pass */
1766int x264_ratecontrol_slice_type( x264_t *h, int frame_num )
1767{
1768 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1769 if( h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
1770 {
1771 if( frame_num >= rc->num_entries )
1772 {
1773 /* We could try to initialize everything required for ABR and
1774 * adaptive B-frames, but that would be complicated.
1775 * So just calculate the average QP used so far. */
1776 h->param.rc.i_qp_constant = (h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P] == 0) ? 24 + QP_BD_OFFSET
1777 : 1 + h->stat.f_frame_qp[SLICE_TYPE_P] / h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P];
1778 rc->qp_constant[SLICE_TYPE_P] = x264_clip3( h->param.rc.i_qp_constant, 0, QP_MAX );
1779 rc->qp_constant[SLICE_TYPE_I] = x264_clip3( (int)( qscale2qp( qp2qscale( h->param.rc.i_qp_constant ) / h->param.rc.f_ip_factor ) + 0.5 ), 0, QP_MAX );
1780 rc->qp_constant[SLICE_TYPE_B] = x264_clip3( (int)( qscale2qp( qp2qscale( h->param.rc.i_qp_constant ) * h->param.rc.f_pb_factor ) + 0.5 ), 0, QP_MAX );
1781
1782 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "2nd pass has more frames than 1st pass (%d)\n", rc->num_entries );
1783 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "continuing anyway, at constant QP=%d\n", h->param.rc.i_qp_constant );
1784 if( h->param.i_bframe_adaptive )
1785 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "disabling adaptive B-frames\n" );
1786
1787 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
1788 {
1789 h->thread[i]->rc->b_abr = 0;
1790 h->thread[i]->rc->b_2pass = 0;
1791 h->thread[i]->param.rc.i_rc_method = X264_RC_CQP;
1792 h->thread[i]->param.rc.b_stat_read = 0;
1793 h->thread[i]->param.i_bframe_adaptive = 0;
1794 h->thread[i]->param.i_scenecut_threshold = 0;
1795 h->thread[i]->param.rc.b_mb_tree = 0;
1796 if( h->thread[i]->param.i_bframe > 1 )
1797 h->thread[i]->param.i_bframe = 1;
1798 }
1799 return X264_TYPE_AUTO;
1800 }
1801 return rc->entry[frame_num].frame_type;
1802 }
1803 else
1804 return X264_TYPE_AUTO;
1805}
1806
1807void x264_ratecontrol_set_weights( x264_t *h, x264_frame_t *frm )
1808{
1809 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = &h->rc->entry[frm->i_frame];
1810 if( h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred <= 0 )
1811 return;
1812
1813 if( rce->i_weight_denom[0] >= 0 )
1814 SET_WEIGHT( frm->weight[0][0], 1, rce->weight[0][0], rce->i_weight_denom[0], rce->weight[0][1] );
1815
1816 if( rce->i_weight_denom[1] >= 0 )
1817 {
1818 SET_WEIGHT( frm->weight[0][1], 1, rce->weight[1][0], rce->i_weight_denom[1], rce->weight[1][1] );
1819 SET_WEIGHT( frm->weight[0][2], 1, rce->weight[2][0], rce->i_weight_denom[1], rce->weight[2][1] );
1820 }
1821}
1822
1823/* After encoding one frame, save stats and update ratecontrol state */
1824int x264_ratecontrol_end( x264_t *h, int bits, int *filler )
1825{
1826 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
1827 const int *mbs = h->stat.frame.i_mb_count;
1828
1829 x264_emms();
1830
1831 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_skip = mbs[P_SKIP] + mbs[B_SKIP];
1832 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_i = mbs[I_16x16] + mbs[I_8x8] + mbs[I_4x4] + mbs[I_PCM];
1833 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_p = mbs[P_L0] + mbs[P_8x8];
1834 for( int i = B_DIRECT; i <= B_8x8; i++ )
1835 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_p += mbs[i];
1836
1837 h->fdec->f_qp_avg_rc = rc->qpa_rc /= h->mb.i_mb_count;
1838 h->fdec->f_qp_avg_aq = (float)rc->qpa_aq / h->mb.i_mb_count;
1839 h->fdec->f_crf_avg = h->param.rc.f_rf_constant + h->fdec->f_qp_avg_rc - rc->qp_novbv;
1840
1841 if( h->param.rc.b_stat_write )
1842 {
1843 char c_type = h->sh.i_type==SLICE_TYPE_I ? (h->fenc->i_poc==0 ? 'I' : 'i')
1844 : h->sh.i_type==SLICE_TYPE_P ? 'P'
1845 : h->fenc->b_kept_as_ref ? 'B' : 'b';
1846 int dir_frame = h->stat.frame.i_direct_score[1] - h->stat.frame.i_direct_score[0];
1847 int dir_avg = h->stat.i_direct_score[1] - h->stat.i_direct_score[0];
1848 char c_direct = h->mb.b_direct_auto_write ?
1849 ( dir_frame>0 ? 's' : dir_frame<0 ? 't' :
1850 dir_avg>0 ? 's' : dir_avg<0 ? 't' : '-' )
1851 : '-';
1852 if( fprintf( rc->p_stat_file_out,
1853 "in:%d out:%d type:%c dur:%"PRId64" cpbdur:%"PRId64" q:%.2f aq:%.2f tex:%d mv:%d misc:%d imb:%d pmb:%d smb:%d d:%c ref:",
1854 h->fenc->i_frame, h->i_frame,
1855 c_type, h->fenc->i_duration,
1856 h->fenc->i_cpb_duration,
1857 rc->qpa_rc, h->fdec->f_qp_avg_aq,
1858 h->stat.frame.i_tex_bits,
1859 h->stat.frame.i_mv_bits,
1860 h->stat.frame.i_misc_bits,
1861 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_i,
1862 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_p,
1863 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_skip,
1864 c_direct) < 0 )
1865 goto fail;
1866
1867 /* Only write information for reference reordering once. */
1868 int use_old_stats = h->param.rc.b_stat_read && rc->rce->refs > 1;
1869 for( int i = 0; i < (use_old_stats ? rc->rce->refs : h->i_ref[0]); i++ )
1870 {
1871 int refcount = use_old_stats ? rc->rce->refcount[i]
1872 : PARAM_INTERLACED ? h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_ref[0][i*2]
1873 + h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_ref[0][i*2+1]
1874 : h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_ref[0][i];
1875 if( fprintf( rc->p_stat_file_out, "%d ", refcount ) < 0 )
1876 goto fail;
1877 }
1878
1879 if( h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred >= X264_WEIGHTP_SIMPLE && h->sh.weight[0][0].weightfn )
1880 {
1881 if( fprintf( rc->p_stat_file_out, "w:%d,%d,%d",
1882 h->sh.weight[0][0].i_denom, h->sh.weight[0][0].i_scale, h->sh.weight[0][0].i_offset ) < 0 )
1883 goto fail;
1884 if( h->sh.weight[0][1].weightfn || h->sh.weight[0][2].weightfn )
1885 {
1886 if( fprintf( rc->p_stat_file_out, ",%d,%d,%d,%d,%d ",
1887 h->sh.weight[0][1].i_denom, h->sh.weight[0][1].i_scale, h->sh.weight[0][1].i_offset,
1888 h->sh.weight[0][2].i_scale, h->sh.weight[0][2].i_offset ) < 0 )
1889 goto fail;
1890 }
1891 else if( fprintf( rc->p_stat_file_out, " " ) < 0 )
1892 goto fail;
1893 }
1894
1895 if( fprintf( rc->p_stat_file_out, ";\n") < 0 )
1896 goto fail;
1897
1898 /* Don't re-write the data in multi-pass mode. */
1899 if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree && h->fenc->b_kept_as_ref && !h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
1900 {
1901 uint8_t i_type = h->sh.i_type;
1902 h->mc.mbtree_fix8_pack( rc->mbtree.qp_buffer[0], h->fenc->f_qp_offset, h->mb.i_mb_count );
1903 if( fwrite( &i_type, 1, 1, rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_out ) < 1 )
1904 goto fail;
1905 if( fwrite( rc->mbtree.qp_buffer[0], sizeof(uint16_t), h->mb.i_mb_count, rc->p_mbtree_stat_file_out ) < (unsigned)h->mb.i_mb_count )
1906 goto fail;
1907 }
1908 }
1909
1910 if( rc->b_abr )
1911 {
1912 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_B )
1913 rc->cplxr_sum += bits * qp2qscale( rc->qpa_rc ) / rc->last_rceq;
1914 else
1915 {
1916 /* Depends on the fact that B-frame's QP is an offset from the following P-frame's.
1917 * Not perfectly accurate with B-refs, but good enough. */
1918 rc->cplxr_sum += bits * qp2qscale( rc->qpa_rc ) / (rc->last_rceq * h->param.rc.f_pb_factor);
1919 }
1920 rc->cplxr_sum *= rc->cbr_decay;
1921 rc->wanted_bits_window += h->fenc->f_duration * rc->bitrate;
1922 rc->wanted_bits_window *= rc->cbr_decay;
1923 }
1924
1925 if( rc->b_2pass )
1926 rc->expected_bits_sum += qscale2bits( rc->rce, qp2qscale( rc->rce->new_qp ) );
1927
1928 if( h->mb.b_variable_qp )
1929 {
1930 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
1931 {
1932 rc->bframe_bits += bits;
1933 if( h->fenc->b_last_minigop_bframe )
1934 {
1935 update_predictor( rc->pred_b_from_p, qp2qscale( rc->qpa_rc ),
1936 h->fref[1][h->i_ref[1]-1]->i_satd, rc->bframe_bits / rc->bframes );
1937 rc->bframe_bits = 0;
1938 }
1939 }
1940 }
1941
1942 *filler = update_vbv( h, bits );
1943 rc->filler_bits_sum += *filler * 8;
1944
1945 if( h->sps->vui.b_nal_hrd_parameters_present )
1946 {
1947 if( h->fenc->i_frame == 0 )
1948 {
1949 // access unit initialises the HRD
1950 h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_initial_arrival_time = 0;
1951 rc->initial_cpb_removal_delay = h->initial_cpb_removal_delay;
1952 rc->initial_cpb_removal_delay_offset = h->initial_cpb_removal_delay_offset;
1953 h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_removal_time = rc->nrt_first_access_unit = (double)rc->initial_cpb_removal_delay / 90000;
1954 }
1955 else
1956 {
1957 h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_removal_time = rc->nrt_first_access_unit + (double)(h->fenc->i_cpb_delay - h->i_cpb_delay_pir_offset) *
1958 h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
1959
1960 if( h->fenc->b_keyframe )
1961 {
1962 rc->nrt_first_access_unit = h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_removal_time;
1963 rc->initial_cpb_removal_delay = h->initial_cpb_removal_delay;
1964 rc->initial_cpb_removal_delay_offset = h->initial_cpb_removal_delay_offset;
1965 }
1966
1967 double cpb_earliest_arrival_time = h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_removal_time - (double)rc->initial_cpb_removal_delay / 90000;
1968 if( !h->fenc->b_keyframe )
1969 cpb_earliest_arrival_time -= (double)rc->initial_cpb_removal_delay_offset / 90000;
1970
1971 if( h->sps->vui.hrd.b_cbr_hrd )
1972 h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_initial_arrival_time = rc->previous_cpb_final_arrival_time;
1973 else
1974 h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_initial_arrival_time = X264_MAX( rc->previous_cpb_final_arrival_time, cpb_earliest_arrival_time );
1975 }
1976 int filler_bits = *filler ? X264_MAX( (FILLER_OVERHEAD - h->param.b_annexb), *filler )*8 : 0;
1977 // Equation C-6
1978 h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_final_arrival_time = rc->previous_cpb_final_arrival_time = h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_initial_arrival_time +
1979 (double)(bits + filler_bits) / h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled;
1980
1981 h->fenc->hrd_timing.dpb_output_time = (double)h->fenc->i_dpb_output_delay * h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale +
1982 h->fenc->hrd_timing.cpb_removal_time;
1983 }
1984
1985 return 0;
1986fail:
1987 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "ratecontrol_end: stats file could not be written to\n" );
1988 return -1;
1989}

1992 * 2 pass functions
1993 ***************************************************************************/
