1995/**
1996 * modify the bitrate curve from pass1 for one frame
1997 */
1998static double get_qscale(x264_t *h, ratecontrol_entry_t *rce, double rate_factor, int frame_num)
1999{
2000 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc= h->rc;
2001 x264_zone_t *zone = get_zone( h, frame_num );
2002 double q;
2003 if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree )
2004 {
2005 double timescale = (double)h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2006 q = pow( BASE_FRAME_DURATION / CLIP_DURATION(rce->i_duration * timescale), 1 - h->param.rc.f_qcompress );
2007 }
2008 else
2009 q = pow( rce->blurred_complexity, 1 - rcc->qcompress );
2010
2011 // avoid NaN's in the rc_eq
2012 if( !isfinite(q) || rce->tex_bits + rce->mv_bits == 0 )
2013 q = rcc->last_qscale_for[rce->pict_type];
2014 else
2015 {
2016 rcc->last_rceq = q;
2017 q /= rate_factor;
2018 rcc->last_qscale = q;
2019 }
2020
2021 if( zone )
2022 {
2023 if( zone->b_force_qp )
2024 q = qp2qscale( zone->i_qp );
2025 else
2026 q /= zone->f_bitrate_factor;
2027 }
2028
2029 return q;
2030}
2031
2032static double get_diff_limited_q(x264_t *h, ratecontrol_entry_t *rce, double q, int frame_num)
2033{
2034 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2035 const int pict_type = rce->pict_type;
2036 x264_zone_t *zone = get_zone( h, frame_num );
2037
2038 // force I/B quants as a function of P quants
2039 if( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_I )
2040 {
2041 double iq = q;
2042 double pq = qp2qscale( rcc->accum_p_qp / rcc->accum_p_norm );
2043 double ip_factor = h->param.rc.f_ip_factor;
2044 /* don't apply ip_factor if the following frame is also I */
2045 if( rcc->accum_p_norm <= 0 )
2046 q = iq;
2047 else if( rcc->accum_p_norm >= 1 )
2048 q = pq / ip_factor;
2049 else
2050 q = rcc->accum_p_norm * pq / ip_factor + (1 - rcc->accum_p_norm) * iq;
2051 }
2052 else if( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
2053 {
2054 q = rcc->last_qscale_for[rcc->last_non_b_pict_type];
2055 if( !rce->kept_as_ref )
2056 q *= h->param.rc.f_pb_factor;
2057 }
2058 else if( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_P
2059 && rcc->last_non_b_pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_P
2060 && rce->tex_bits == 0 )
2061 {
2062 q = rcc->last_qscale_for[SLICE_TYPE_P];
2063 }
2064
2065 /* last qscale / qdiff stuff */
2066 if( rcc->last_non_b_pict_type == pict_type &&
2067 (pict_type!=SLICE_TYPE_I || rcc->last_accum_p_norm < 1) )
2068 {
2069 double last_q = rcc->last_qscale_for[pict_type];
2070 double max_qscale = last_q * rcc->lstep;
2071 double min_qscale = last_q / rcc->lstep;
2072
2073 if ( q > max_qscale ) q = max_qscale;
2074 else if( q < min_qscale ) q = min_qscale;
2075 }
2076
2077 rcc->last_qscale_for[pict_type] = q;
2078 if( pict_type != SLICE_TYPE_B )
2079 rcc->last_non_b_pict_type = pict_type;
2080 if( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_I )
2081 {
2082 rcc->last_accum_p_norm = rcc->accum_p_norm;
2083 rcc->accum_p_norm = 0;
2084 rcc->accum_p_qp = 0;
2085 }
2086 if( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_P )
2087 {
2088 float mask = 1 - pow( (float)rce->i_count / rcc->nmb, 2 );
2089 rcc->accum_p_qp = mask * (qscale2qp( q ) + rcc->accum_p_qp);
2090 rcc->accum_p_norm = mask * (1 + rcc->accum_p_norm);
2091 }
2092
2093 if( zone )
2094 {
2095 if( zone->b_force_qp )
2096 q = qp2qscale( zone->i_qp );
2097 else
2098 q /= zone->f_bitrate_factor;
2099 }
2100
2101 return q;
2102}
2103
2104static float predict_size( predictor_t *p, float q, float var )
2105{
2106 return (p->coeff*var + p->offset) / (q*p->count);
2107}
2108
2109static void update_predictor( predictor_t *p, float q, float var, float bits )
2110{
2111 float range = 1.5;
2112 if( var < 10 )
2113 return;
2114 float old_coeff = p->coeff / p->count;
2115 float old_offset = p->offset / p->count;
2116 float new_coeff = X264_MAX( (bits*q - old_offset) / var, p->coeff_min );
2117 float new_coeff_clipped = x264_clip3f( new_coeff, old_coeff/range, old_coeff*range );
2118 float new_offset = bits*q - new_coeff_clipped * var;
2119 if( new_offset >= 0 )
2120 new_coeff = new_coeff_clipped;
2121 else
2122 new_offset = 0;
2123 p->count *= p->decay;
2124 p->coeff *= p->decay;
2125 p->offset *= p->decay;
2126 p->count ++;
2127 p->coeff += new_coeff;
2128 p->offset += new_offset;
2129}
2130
2131// update VBV after encoding a frame
2132static int update_vbv( x264_t *h, int bits )
2133{
2134 int filler = 0;
2135 int bitrate = h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled;
2136 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2137 x264_ratecontrol_t *rct = h->thread[0]->rc;
2138 int64_t buffer_size = (int64_t)h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_unscaled * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2139
2140 if( rcc->last_satd >= h->mb.i_mb_count )
2141 update_predictor( &rct->pred[h->sh.i_type], qp2qscale( rcc->qpa_rc ), rcc->last_satd, bits );
2142
2143 if( !rcc->b_vbv )
2144 return filler;
2145
2146 uint64_t buffer_diff = (uint64_t)bits * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2147 rct->buffer_fill_final -= buffer_diff;
2148 rct->buffer_fill_final_min -= buffer_diff;
2149
2150 if( rct->buffer_fill_final_min < 0 )
2151 {
2152 double underflow = (double)rct->buffer_fill_final_min / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2153 if( rcc->rate_factor_max_increment && rcc->qpm >= rcc->qp_novbv + rcc->rate_factor_max_increment )
2154 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_DEBUG, "VBV underflow due to CRF-max (frame %d, %.0f bits)\n", h->i_frame, underflow );
2155 else
2156 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "VBV underflow (frame %d, %.0f bits)\n", h->i_frame, underflow );
2157 rct->buffer_fill_final =
2158 rct->buffer_fill_final_min = 0;
2159 }
2160
2161 if( h->param.i_avcintra_class )
2162 buffer_diff = buffer_size;
2163 else
2164 buffer_diff = (uint64_t)bitrate * h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick * h->fenc->i_cpb_duration;
2165 rct->buffer_fill_final += buffer_diff;
2166 rct->buffer_fill_final_min += buffer_diff;
2167
2168 if( rct->buffer_fill_final > buffer_size )
2169 {
2170 if( h->param.rc.b_filler )
2171 {
2172 int64_t scale = (int64_t)h->sps->vui.i_time_scale * 8;
2173 filler = (rct->buffer_fill_final - buffer_size + scale - 1) / scale;
2174 bits = h->param.i_avcintra_class ? filler * 8 : X264_MAX( (FILLER_OVERHEAD - h->param.b_annexb), filler ) * 8;
2175 buffer_diff = (uint64_t)bits * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2176 rct->buffer_fill_final -= buffer_diff;
2177 rct->buffer_fill_final_min -= buffer_diff;
2178 }
2179 else
2180 {
2181 rct->buffer_fill_final = X264_MIN( rct->buffer_fill_final, buffer_size );
2182 rct->buffer_fill_final_min = X264_MIN( rct->buffer_fill_final_min, buffer_size );
2183 }
2184 }
2185
2186 return filler;
2187}
2188
2189void x264_hrd_fullness( x264_t *h )
2190{
2191 x264_ratecontrol_t *rct = h->thread[0]->rc;
2192 uint64_t denom = (uint64_t)h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale / rct->hrd_multiply_denom;
2193 uint64_t cpb_state = rct->buffer_fill_final;
2194 uint64_t cpb_size = (uint64_t)h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_unscaled * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2195 uint64_t multiply_factor = 90000 / rct->hrd_multiply_denom;
2196
2197 if( rct->buffer_fill_final < 0 || rct->buffer_fill_final > (int64_t)cpb_size )
2198 {
2199 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "CPB %s: %.0f bits in a %.0f-bit buffer\n",
2200 rct->buffer_fill_final < 0 ? "underflow" : "overflow",
2201 (double)rct->buffer_fill_final / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale, (double)cpb_size / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale );
2202 }
2203
2204 h->initial_cpb_removal_delay = (multiply_factor * cpb_state) / denom;
2205 h->initial_cpb_removal_delay_offset = (multiply_factor * cpb_size) / denom - h->initial_cpb_removal_delay;
2206
2207 int64_t decoder_buffer_fill = h->initial_cpb_removal_delay * denom / multiply_factor;
2208 rct->buffer_fill_final_min = X264_MIN( rct->buffer_fill_final_min, decoder_buffer_fill );
2209}
2210
2211// provisionally update VBV according to the planned size of all frames currently in progress
2212static void update_vbv_plan( x264_t *h, int overhead )
2213{
2214 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2215 rcc->buffer_fill = h->thread[0]->rc->buffer_fill_final_min / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2216 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
2217 {
2218 int j = rcc - h->thread[0]->rc;
2219 for( int i = 1; i < h->i_thread_frames; i++ )
2220 {
2221 x264_t *t = h->thread[ (j+i)%h->i_thread_frames ];
2222 double bits = t->rc->frame_size_planned;
2223 if( !t->b_thread_active )
2224 continue;
2225 bits = X264_MAX(bits, t->rc->frame_size_estimated);
2226 rcc->buffer_fill -= bits;
2227 rcc->buffer_fill = X264_MAX( rcc->buffer_fill, 0 );
2228 rcc->buffer_fill += t->rc->buffer_rate;
2229 rcc->buffer_fill = X264_MIN( rcc->buffer_fill, rcc->buffer_size );
2230 }
2231 }
2232 rcc->buffer_fill = X264_MIN( rcc->buffer_fill, rcc->buffer_size );
2233 rcc->buffer_fill -= overhead;
2234}
2235
2236// apply VBV constraints and clip qscale to between lmin and lmax
2237static double clip_qscale( x264_t *h, int pict_type, double q )
2238{
2239 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2240 double lmin = rcc->lmin[pict_type];
2241 double lmax = rcc->lmax[pict_type];
2242 if( rcc->rate_factor_max_increment )
2243 lmax = X264_MIN( lmax, qp2qscale( rcc->qp_novbv + rcc->rate_factor_max_increment ) );
2244 double q0 = q;
2245
2246 /* B-frames are not directly subject to VBV,
2247 * since they are controlled by the P-frames' QPs. */
2248
2249 if( rcc->b_vbv && rcc->last_satd > 0 )
2250 {
2251 double fenc_cpb_duration = (double)h->fenc->i_cpb_duration *
2252 h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2253 /* Lookahead VBV: raise the quantizer as necessary such that no frames in
2254 * the lookahead overflow and such that the buffer is in a reasonable state
2255 * by the end of the lookahead. */
2256 if( h->param.rc.i_lookahead )
2257 {
2258 int terminate = 0;
2259
2260 /* Avoid an infinite loop. */
2261 for( int iterations = 0; iterations < 1000 && terminate != 3; iterations++ )
2262 {
2263 double frame_q[3];
2264 double cur_bits = predict_size( &rcc->pred[h->sh.i_type], q, rcc->last_satd );
2265 double buffer_fill_cur = rcc->buffer_fill - cur_bits;
2266 double target_fill;
2267 double total_duration = 0;
2268 double last_duration = fenc_cpb_duration;
2269 frame_q[0] = h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_I ? q * h->param.rc.f_ip_factor : q;
2270 frame_q[1] = frame_q[0] * h->param.rc.f_pb_factor;
2271 frame_q[2] = frame_q[0] / h->param.rc.f_ip_factor;
2272
2273 /* Loop over the planned future frames. */
2274 for( int j = 0; buffer_fill_cur >= 0 && buffer_fill_cur <= rcc->buffer_size; j++ )
2275 {
2276 total_duration += last_duration;
2277 buffer_fill_cur += rcc->vbv_max_rate * last_duration;
2278 int i_type = h->fenc->i_planned_type[j];
2279 int i_satd = h->fenc->i_planned_satd[j];
2280 if( i_type == X264_TYPE_AUTO )
2281 break;
2282 i_type = IS_X264_TYPE_I( i_type ) ? SLICE_TYPE_I : IS_X264_TYPE_B( i_type ) ? SLICE_TYPE_B : SLICE_TYPE_P;
2283 cur_bits = predict_size( &rcc->pred[i_type], frame_q[i_type], i_satd );
2284 buffer_fill_cur -= cur_bits;
2285 last_duration = h->fenc->f_planned_cpb_duration[j];
2286 }
2287 /* Try to get to get the buffer at least 50% filled, but don't set an impossible goal. */
2288 target_fill = X264_MIN( rcc->buffer_fill + total_duration * rcc->vbv_max_rate * 0.5, rcc->buffer_size * 0.5 );
2289 if( buffer_fill_cur < target_fill )
2290 {
2291 q *= 1.01;
2292 terminate |= 1;
2293 continue;
2294 }
2295 /* Try to get the buffer no more than 80% filled, but don't set an impossible goal. */
2296 target_fill = x264_clip3f( rcc->buffer_fill - total_duration * rcc->vbv_max_rate * 0.5, rcc->buffer_size * 0.8, rcc->buffer_size );
2297 if( rcc->b_vbv_min_rate && buffer_fill_cur > target_fill )
2298 {
2299 q /= 1.01;
2300 terminate |= 2;
2301 continue;
2302 }
2303 break;
2304 }
2305 }
2306 /* Fallback to old purely-reactive algorithm: no lookahead. */
2307 else
2308 {
2309 if( ( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_P ||
2310 ( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_I && rcc->last_non_b_pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_I ) ) &&
2311 rcc->buffer_fill/rcc->buffer_size < 0.5 )
2312 {
2313 q /= x264_clip3f( 2.0*rcc->buffer_fill/rcc->buffer_size, 0.5, 1.0 );
2314 }
2315
2316 /* Now a hard threshold to make sure the frame fits in VBV.
2317 * This one is mostly for I-frames. */
2318 double bits = predict_size( &rcc->pred[h->sh.i_type], q, rcc->last_satd );
2319 /* For small VBVs, allow the frame to use up the entire VBV. */
2320 double max_fill_factor = h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size >= 5*h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate / rcc->fps ? 2 : 1;
2321 /* For single-frame VBVs, request that the frame use up the entire VBV. */
2322 double min_fill_factor = rcc->single_frame_vbv ? 1 : 2;
2323
2324 if( bits > rcc->buffer_fill/max_fill_factor )
2325 {
2326 double qf = x264_clip3f( rcc->buffer_fill/(max_fill_factor*bits), 0.2, 1.0 );
2327 q /= qf;
2328 bits *= qf;
2329 }
2330 if( bits < rcc->buffer_rate/min_fill_factor )
2331 {
2332 double qf = x264_clip3f( bits*min_fill_factor/rcc->buffer_rate, 0.001, 1.0 );
2333 q *= qf;
2334 }
2335 q = X264_MAX( q0, q );
2336 }
2337
2338 /* Check B-frame complexity, and use up any bits that would
2339 * overflow before the next P-frame. */
2340 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_P && !rcc->single_frame_vbv )
2341 {
2342 int nb = rcc->bframes;
2343 double bits = predict_size( &rcc->pred[h->sh.i_type], q, rcc->last_satd );
2344 double pbbits = bits;
2345 double bbits = predict_size( rcc->pred_b_from_p, q * h->param.rc.f_pb_factor, rcc->last_satd );
2346 double space;
2347 double bframe_cpb_duration = 0;
2348 double minigop_cpb_duration;
2349 for( int i = 0; i < nb; i++ )
2350 bframe_cpb_duration += h->fenc->f_planned_cpb_duration[i];
2351
2352 if( bbits * nb > bframe_cpb_duration * rcc->vbv_max_rate )
2353 {
2354 nb = 0;
2355 bframe_cpb_duration = 0;
2356 }
2357 pbbits += nb * bbits;
2358
2359 minigop_cpb_duration = bframe_cpb_duration + fenc_cpb_duration;
2360 space = rcc->buffer_fill + minigop_cpb_duration*rcc->vbv_max_rate - rcc->buffer_size;
2361 if( pbbits < space )
2362 {
2363 q *= X264_MAX( pbbits / space, bits / (0.5 * rcc->buffer_size) );
2364 }
2365 q = X264_MAX( q0/2, q );
2366 }
2367
2368 /* Apply MinCR and buffer fill restrictions */
2369 double bits = predict_size( &rcc->pred[h->sh.i_type], q, rcc->last_satd );
2370 double frame_size_maximum = X264_MIN( rcc->frame_size_maximum, X264_MAX( rcc->buffer_fill, 0.001 ) );
2371 if( bits > frame_size_maximum )
2372 q *= bits / frame_size_maximum;
2373
2374 if( !rcc->b_vbv_min_rate )
2375 q = X264_MAX( q0, q );
2376 }
2377
2378 if( lmin==lmax )
2379 return lmin;
2380 else if( rcc->b_2pass )
2381 {
2382 double min2 = log( lmin );
2383 double max2 = log( lmax );
2384 q = (log(q) - min2)/(max2-min2) - 0.5;
2385 q = 1.0/(1.0 + exp( -4*q ));
2386 q = q*(max2-min2) + min2;
2387 return exp( q );
2388 }
2389 else
2390 return x264_clip3f( q, lmin, lmax );
2391}
2392
2393// update qscale for 1 frame based on actual bits used so far
2394static float rate_estimate_qscale( x264_t *h )
2395{
2396 float q;
2397 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2398 ratecontrol_entry_t rce = {0};
2399 int pict_type = h->sh.i_type;
2400 int64_t total_bits = 8*(h->stat.i_frame_size[SLICE_TYPE_I]
2401 + h->stat.i_frame_size[SLICE_TYPE_P]
2402 + h->stat.i_frame_size[SLICE_TYPE_B])
2403 - rcc->filler_bits_sum;
2404
2405 if( rcc->b_2pass )
2406 {
2407 rce = *rcc->rce;
2408 if( pict_type != rce.pict_type )
2409 {
2410 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "slice=%c but 2pass stats say %c\n",
2411 slice_type_to_char[pict_type], slice_type_to_char[rce.pict_type] );
2412 }
2413 }
2414
2415 if( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
2416 {
2417 /* B-frames don't have independent ratecontrol, but rather get the
2418 * average QP of the two adjacent P-frames + an offset */
2419
2420 int i0 = IS_X264_TYPE_I(h->fref_nearest[0]->i_type);
2421 int i1 = IS_X264_TYPE_I(h->fref_nearest[1]->i_type);
2422 int dt0 = abs(h->fenc->i_poc - h->fref_nearest[0]->i_poc);
2423 int dt1 = abs(h->fenc->i_poc - h->fref_nearest[1]->i_poc);
2424 float q0 = h->fref_nearest[0]->f_qp_avg_rc;
2425 float q1 = h->fref_nearest[1]->f_qp_avg_rc;
2426
2427 if( h->fref_nearest[0]->i_type == X264_TYPE_BREF )
2428 q0 -= rcc->pb_offset/2;
2429 if( h->fref_nearest[1]->i_type == X264_TYPE_BREF )
2430 q1 -= rcc->pb_offset/2;
2431
2432 if( i0 && i1 )
2433 q = (q0 + q1) / 2 + rcc->ip_offset;
2434 else if( i0 )
2435 q = q1;
2436 else if( i1 )
2437 q = q0;
2438 else
2439 q = (q0*dt1 + q1*dt0) / (dt0 + dt1);
2440
2441 if( h->fenc->b_kept_as_ref )
2442 q += rcc->pb_offset/2;
2443 else
2444 q += rcc->pb_offset;
2445
2446 rcc->qp_novbv = q;
2447 q = qp2qscale( q );
2448 if( rcc->b_2pass )
2449 rcc->frame_size_planned = qscale2bits( &rce, q );
2450 else
2451 rcc->frame_size_planned = predict_size( rcc->pred_b_from_p, q, h->fref[1][h->i_ref[1]-1]->i_satd );
2452 /* Limit planned size by MinCR */
2453 if( rcc->b_vbv )
2454 rcc->frame_size_planned = X264_MIN( rcc->frame_size_planned, rcc->frame_size_maximum );
2455 rcc->frame_size_estimated = rcc->frame_size_planned;
2456
2457 /* For row SATDs */
2458 if( rcc->b_vbv )
2459 rcc->last_satd = x264_rc_analyse_slice( h );
2460 return q;
2461 }
2462 else
2463 {
2464 double abr_buffer = 2 * rcc->rate_tolerance * rcc->bitrate;
2465 double predicted_bits = total_bits;
2466 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
2467 {
2468 int j = rcc - h->thread[0]->rc;
2469 for( int i = 1; i < h->i_thread_frames; i++ )
2470 {
2471 x264_t *t = h->thread[(j+i) % h->i_thread_frames];
2472 double bits = t->rc->frame_size_planned;
2473 if( !t->b_thread_active )
2474 continue;
2475 bits = X264_MAX(bits, t->rc->frame_size_estimated);
2476 predicted_bits += bits;
2477 }
2478 }
2479
2480 if( rcc->b_2pass )
2481 {
2482 double lmin = rcc->lmin[pict_type];
2483 double lmax = rcc->lmax[pict_type];
2484 double diff;
2485
2486 /* Adjust ABR buffer based on distance to the end of the video. */
2487 if( rcc->num_entries > h->i_frame )
2488 {
2489 double final_bits = rcc->entry_out[rcc->num_entries-1]->expected_bits;
2490 double video_pos = rce.expected_bits / final_bits;
2491 double scale_factor = sqrt( (1 - video_pos) * rcc->num_entries );
2492 abr_buffer *= 0.5 * X264_MAX( scale_factor, 0.5 );
2493 }
2494
2495 diff = predicted_bits - rce.expected_bits;
2496 q = rce.new_qscale;
2497 q /= x264_clip3f((abr_buffer - diff) / abr_buffer, .5, 2);
2498 if( h->i_frame >= rcc->fps && rcc->expected_bits_sum >= 1 )
2499 {
2500 /* Adjust quant based on the difference between
2501 * achieved and expected bitrate so far */
2502 double cur_time = (double)h->i_frame / rcc->num_entries;
2503 double w = x264_clip3f( cur_time*100, 0.0, 1.0 );
2504 q *= pow( (double)total_bits / rcc->expected_bits_sum, w );
2505 }
2506 rcc->qp_novbv = qscale2qp( q );
2507 if( rcc->b_vbv )
2508 {
2509 /* Do not overflow vbv */
2510 double expected_size = qscale2bits( &rce, q );
2511 double expected_vbv = rcc->buffer_fill + rcc->buffer_rate - expected_size;
2512 double expected_fullness = rce.expected_vbv / rcc->buffer_size;
2513 double qmax = q*(2 - expected_fullness);
2514 double size_constraint = 1 + expected_fullness;
2515 qmax = X264_MAX( qmax, rce.new_qscale );
2516 if( expected_fullness < .05 )
2517 qmax = lmax;
2518 qmax = X264_MIN(qmax, lmax);
2519 while( ((expected_vbv < rce.expected_vbv/size_constraint) && (q < qmax)) ||
2520 ((expected_vbv < 0) && (q < lmax)))
2521 {
2522 q *= 1.05;
2523 expected_size = qscale2bits(&rce, q);
2524 expected_vbv = rcc->buffer_fill + rcc->buffer_rate - expected_size;
2525 }
2526 rcc->last_satd = x264_rc_analyse_slice( h );
2527 }
2528 q = x264_clip3f( q, lmin, lmax );
2529 }
2530 else /* 1pass ABR */
2531 {
2532 /* Calculate the quantizer which would have produced the desired
2533 * average bitrate if it had been applied to all frames so far.
2534 * Then modulate that quant based on the current frame's complexity
2535 * relative to the average complexity so far (using the 2pass RCEQ).
2536 * Then bias the quant up or down if total size so far was far from
2537 * the target.
2538 * Result: Depending on the value of rate_tolerance, there is a
2539 * tradeoff between quality and bitrate precision. But at large
2540 * tolerances, the bit distribution approaches that of 2pass. */
2541
2542 double wanted_bits, overflow = 1;
2543
2544 rcc->last_satd = x264_rc_analyse_slice( h );
2545 rcc->short_term_cplxsum *= 0.5;
2546 rcc->short_term_cplxcount *= 0.5;
2547 rcc->short_term_cplxsum += rcc->last_satd / (CLIP_DURATION(h->fenc->f_duration) / BASE_FRAME_DURATION);
2548 rcc->short_term_cplxcount ++;
2549
2550 rce.tex_bits = rcc->last_satd;
2551 rce.blurred_complexity = rcc->short_term_cplxsum / rcc->short_term_cplxcount;
2552 rce.mv_bits = 0;
2553 rce.p_count = rcc->nmb;
2554 rce.i_count = 0;
2555 rce.s_count = 0;
2556 rce.qscale = 1;
2557 rce.pict_type = pict_type;
2558 rce.i_duration = h->fenc->i_duration;
2559
2560 if( h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_CRF )
2561 {
2562 q = get_qscale( h, &rce, rcc->rate_factor_constant, h->fenc->i_frame );
2563 }
2564 else
2565 {
2566 q = get_qscale( h, &rce, rcc->wanted_bits_window / rcc->cplxr_sum, h->fenc->i_frame );
2567
2568 /* ABR code can potentially be counterproductive in CBR, so just don't bother.
2569 * Don't run it if the frame complexity is zero either. */
2570 if( !rcc->b_vbv_min_rate && rcc->last_satd )
2571 {
2572 // FIXME is it simpler to keep track of wanted_bits in ratecontrol_end?
2573 int i_frame_done = h->i_frame;
2574 double time_done = i_frame_done / rcc->fps;
2575 if( h->param.b_vfr_input && i_frame_done > 0 )
2576 time_done = ((double)(h->fenc->i_reordered_pts - h->i_reordered_pts_delay)) * h->param.i_timebase_num / h->param.i_timebase_den;
2577 wanted_bits = time_done * rcc->bitrate;
2578 if( wanted_bits > 0 )
2579 {
2580 abr_buffer *= X264_MAX( 1, sqrt( time_done ) );
2581 overflow = x264_clip3f( 1.0 + (predicted_bits - wanted_bits) / abr_buffer, .5, 2 );
2582 q *= overflow;
2583 }
2584 }
2585 }
2586
2587 if( pict_type == SLICE_TYPE_I && h->param.i_keyint_max > 1
2588 /* should test _next_ pict type, but that isn't decided yet */
2589 && rcc->last_non_b_pict_type != SLICE_TYPE_I )
2590 {
2591 q = qp2qscale( rcc->accum_p_qp / rcc->accum_p_norm );
2592 q /= h->param.rc.f_ip_factor;
2593 }
2594 else if( h->i_frame > 0 )
2595 {
2596 if( h->param.rc.i_rc_method != X264_RC_CRF )
2597 {
2598 /* Asymmetric clipping, because symmetric would prevent
2599 * overflow control in areas of rapidly oscillating complexity */
2600 double lmin = rcc->last_qscale_for[pict_type] / rcc->lstep;
2601 double lmax = rcc->last_qscale_for[pict_type] * rcc->lstep;
2602 if( overflow > 1.1 && h->i_frame > 3 )
2603 lmax *= rcc->lstep;
2604 else if( overflow < 0.9 )
2605 lmin /= rcc->lstep;
2606
2607 q = x264_clip3f(q, lmin, lmax);
2608 }
2609 }
2610 else if( h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_CRF && rcc->qcompress != 1 )
2611 {
2612 q = qp2qscale( ABR_INIT_QP ) / h->param.rc.f_ip_factor;
2613 }
2614 rcc->qp_novbv = qscale2qp( q );
2615
2616 //FIXME use get_diff_limited_q() ?
2617 q = clip_qscale( h, pict_type, q );
2618 }
2619
2620 rcc->last_qscale_for[pict_type] =
2621 rcc->last_qscale = q;
2622
2623 if( !(rcc->b_2pass && !rcc->b_vbv) && h->fenc->i_frame == 0 )
2624 rcc->last_qscale_for[SLICE_TYPE_P] = q * h->param.rc.f_ip_factor;
2625
2626 if( rcc->b_2pass )
2627 rcc->frame_size_planned = qscale2bits( &rce, q );
2628 else
2629 rcc->frame_size_planned = predict_size( &rcc->pred[h->sh.i_type], q, rcc->last_satd );
2630
2631 /* Always use up the whole VBV in this case. */
2632 if( rcc->single_frame_vbv )
2633 rcc->frame_size_planned = rcc->buffer_rate;
2634 /* Limit planned size by MinCR */
2635 if( rcc->b_vbv )
2636 rcc->frame_size_planned = X264_MIN( rcc->frame_size_planned, rcc->frame_size_maximum );
2637 rcc->frame_size_estimated = rcc->frame_size_planned;
2638 return q;
2639 }
2640}
2641
2642static void threads_normalize_predictors( x264_t *h )
2643{
2644 double totalsize = 0;
2645 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
2646 totalsize += h->thread[i]->rc->slice_size_planned;
2647 double factor = h->rc->frame_size_planned / totalsize;
2648 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
2649 h->thread[i]->rc->slice_size_planned *= factor;
2650}
2651
2652void x264_threads_distribute_ratecontrol( x264_t *h )
2653{
2654 int row;
2655 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
2656 x264_emms();
2657 float qscale = qp2qscale( rc->qpm );
2658
2659 /* Initialize row predictors */
2660 if( h->i_frame == 0 )
2661 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
2662 {
2663 x264_t *t = h->thread[i];
2664 if( t != h )
2665 memcpy( t->rc->row_preds, rc->row_preds, sizeof(rc->row_preds) );
2666 }
2667
2668 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
2669 {
2670 x264_t *t = h->thread[i];
2671 if( t != h )
2672 memcpy( t->rc, rc, offsetof(x264_ratecontrol_t, row_pred) );
2673 t->rc->row_pred = t->rc->row_preds[h->sh.i_type];
2674 /* Calculate the planned slice size. */
2675 if( rc->b_vbv && rc->frame_size_planned )
2676 {
2677 int size = 0;
2678 for( row = t->i_threadslice_start; row < t->i_threadslice_end; row++ )
2679 size += h->fdec->i_row_satd[row];
2680 t->rc->slice_size_planned = predict_size( &rc->pred[h->sh.i_type + (i+1)*5], qscale, size );
2681 }
2682 else
2683 t->rc->slice_size_planned = 0;
2684 }
2685 if( rc->b_vbv && rc->frame_size_planned )
2686 {
2687 threads_normalize_predictors( h );
2688
2689 if( rc->single_frame_vbv )
2690 {
2691 /* Compensate for our max frame error threshold: give more bits (proportionally) to smaller slices. */
2692 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
2693 {
2694 x264_t *t = h->thread[i];
2695 float max_frame_error = x264_clip3f( 1.0 / (t->i_threadslice_end - t->i_threadslice_start), 0.05, 0.25 );
2696 t->rc->slice_size_planned += 2 * max_frame_error * rc->frame_size_planned;
2697 }
2698 threads_normalize_predictors( h );
2699 }
2700
2701 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
2702 h->thread[i]->rc->frame_size_estimated = h->thread[i]->rc->slice_size_planned;
2703 }
2704}
2705
2706void x264_threads_merge_ratecontrol( x264_t *h )
2707{
2708 x264_ratecontrol_t *rc = h->rc;
2709 x264_emms();
2710
2711 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
2712 {
2713 x264_t *t = h->thread[i];
2714 x264_ratecontrol_t *rct = h->thread[i]->rc;
2715 if( h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size )
2716 {
2717 int size = 0;
2718 for( int row = t->i_threadslice_start; row < t->i_threadslice_end; row++ )
2719 size += h->fdec->i_row_satd[row];
2720 int bits = t->stat.frame.i_mv_bits + t->stat.frame.i_tex_bits + t->stat.frame.i_misc_bits;
2721 int mb_count = (t->i_threadslice_end - t->i_threadslice_start) * h->mb.i_mb_width;
2722 update_predictor( &rc->pred[h->sh.i_type+(i+1)*5], qp2qscale( rct->qpa_rc/mb_count ), size, bits );
2723 }
2724 if( !i )
2725 continue;
2726 rc->qpa_rc += rct->qpa_rc;
2727 rc->qpa_aq += rct->qpa_aq;
2728 }
2729}

2731void x264_thread_sync_ratecontrol( x264_t *cur, x264_t *prev, x264_t *next )
2732{
2733 if( cur != prev )
2734 {
2735#define COPY(var) memcpy(&cur->rc->var, &prev->rc->var, sizeof(cur->rc->var))
2736 /* these vars are updated in x264_ratecontrol_start()
2737 * so copy them from the context that most recently started (prev)
2738 * to the context that's about to start (cur). */
2739 COPY(accum_p_qp);
2740 COPY(accum_p_norm);
2741 COPY(last_satd);
2742 COPY(last_rceq);
2743 COPY(last_qscale_for);
2744 COPY(last_non_b_pict_type);
2745 COPY(short_term_cplxsum);
2746 COPY(short_term_cplxcount);
2747 COPY(bframes);
2748 COPY(prev_zone);
2749 COPY(mbtree.qpbuf_pos);
2750 /* these vars can be updated by x264_ratecontrol_init_reconfigurable */
2751 COPY(bitrate);
2752 COPY(buffer_size);
2753 COPY(buffer_rate);
2754 COPY(vbv_max_rate);
2755 COPY(single_frame_vbv);
2756 COPY(cbr_decay);
2757 COPY(rate_factor_constant);
2758 COPY(rate_factor_max_increment);
2759#undef COPY
2760 }
2761 if( cur != next )
2762 {
2763#define COPY(var) next->rc->var = cur->rc->var
2764 /* these vars are updated in x264_ratecontrol_end()
2765 * so copy them from the context that most recently ended (cur)
2766 * to the context that's about to end (next) */
2767 COPY(cplxr_sum);
2768 COPY(expected_bits_sum);
2769 COPY(filler_bits_sum);
2770 COPY(wanted_bits_window);
2771 COPY(bframe_bits);
2772 COPY(initial_cpb_removal_delay);
2773 COPY(initial_cpb_removal_delay_offset);
2774 COPY(nrt_first_access_unit);
2775 COPY(previous_cpb_final_arrival_time);
2776#undef COPY
2777 }
2778 //FIXME row_preds[] (not strictly necessary, but would improve prediction)
2779 /* the rest of the variables are either constant or thread-local */
2780}
2781
2782static int find_underflow( x264_t *h, double *fills, int *t0, int *t1, int over )
2783{
2784 /* find an interval ending on an overflow or underflow (depending on whether
2785 * we're adding or removing bits), and starting on the earliest frame that
2786 * can influence the buffer fill of that end frame. */
2787 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2788 const double buffer_min = .1 * rcc->buffer_size;
2789 const double buffer_max = .9 * rcc->buffer_size;
2790 double fill = fills[*t0-1];
2791 double parity = over ? 1. : -1.;
2792 int start = -1, end = -1;
2793 for( int i = *t0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
2794 {
2795 fill += (rcc->entry_out[i]->i_cpb_duration * rcc->vbv_max_rate * h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale -
2796 qscale2bits( rcc->entry_out[i], rcc->entry_out[i]->new_qscale )) * parity;
2797 fill = x264_clip3f(fill, 0, rcc->buffer_size);
2798 fills[i] = fill;
2799 if( fill <= buffer_min || i == 0 )
2800 {
2801 if( end >= 0 )
2802 break;
2803 start = i;
2804 }
2805 else if( fill >= buffer_max && start >= 0 )
2806 end = i;
2807 }
2808 *t0 = start;
2809 *t1 = end;
2810 return start >= 0 && end >= 0;
2811}
2812
2813static int fix_underflow( x264_t *h, int t0, int t1, double adjustment, double qscale_min, double qscale_max )
2814{
2815 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2816 double qscale_orig, qscale_new;
2817 int adjusted = 0;
2818 if( t0 > 0 )
2819 t0++;
2820 for( int i = t0; i <= t1; i++ )
2821 {
2822 qscale_orig = rcc->entry_out[i]->new_qscale;
2823 qscale_orig = x264_clip3f( qscale_orig, qscale_min, qscale_max );
2824 qscale_new = qscale_orig * adjustment;
2825 qscale_new = x264_clip3f( qscale_new, qscale_min, qscale_max );
2826 rcc->entry_out[i]->new_qscale = qscale_new;
2827 adjusted = adjusted || (qscale_new != qscale_orig);
2828 }
2829 return adjusted;
2830}
2831
2832static double count_expected_bits( x264_t *h )
2833{
2834 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2835 double expected_bits = 0;
2836 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
2837 {
2838 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = rcc->entry_out[i];
2839 rce->expected_bits = expected_bits;
2840 expected_bits += qscale2bits( rce, rce->new_qscale );
2841 }
2842 return expected_bits;
2843}
2844
2845static int vbv_pass2( x264_t *h, double all_available_bits )
2846{
2847 /* for each interval of buffer_full .. underflow, uniformly increase the qp of all
2848 * frames in the interval until either buffer is full at some intermediate frame or the
2849 * last frame in the interval no longer underflows. Recompute intervals and repeat.
2850 * Then do the converse to put bits back into overflow areas until target size is met */
2851
2852 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2853 double *fills;
2854 double expected_bits = 0;
2855 double adjustment;
2856 double prev_bits = 0;
2857 int t0, t1;
2858 double qscale_min = qp2qscale( h->param.rc.i_qp_min );
2859 double qscale_max = qp2qscale( h->param.rc.i_qp_max );
2860 int iterations = 0;
2861 int adj_min, adj_max;
2862 CHECKED_MALLOC( fills, (rcc->num_entries+1)*sizeof(double) );
2863
2864 fills++;
2865
2866 /* adjust overall stream size */
2867 do
2868 {
2869 iterations++;
2870 prev_bits = expected_bits;
2871
2872 if( expected_bits )
2873 { /* not first iteration */
2874 adjustment = X264_MAX(X264_MIN(expected_bits / all_available_bits, 0.999), 0.9);
2875 fills[-1] = rcc->buffer_size * h->param.rc.f_vbv_buffer_init;
2876 t0 = 0;
2877 /* fix overflows */
2878 adj_min = 1;
2879 while( adj_min && find_underflow( h, fills, &t0, &t1, 1 ) )
2880 {
2881 adj_min = fix_underflow( h, t0, t1, adjustment, qscale_min, qscale_max );
2882 t0 = t1;
2883 }
2884 }
2885
2886 fills[-1] = rcc->buffer_size * (1. - h->param.rc.f_vbv_buffer_init);
2887 t0 = 0;
2888 /* fix underflows -- should be done after overflow, as we'd better undersize target than underflowing VBV */
2889 adj_max = 1;
2890 while( adj_max && find_underflow( h, fills, &t0, &t1, 0 ) )
2891 adj_max = fix_underflow( h, t0, t1, 1.001, qscale_min, qscale_max );
2892
2893 expected_bits = count_expected_bits( h );
2894 } while( (expected_bits < .995*all_available_bits) && ((int64_t)(expected_bits+.5) > (int64_t)(prev_bits+.5)) );
2895
2896 if( !adj_max )
2897 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "vbv-maxrate issue, qpmax or vbv-maxrate too low\n");
2898
2899 /* store expected vbv filling values for tracking when encoding */
2900 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
2901 rcc->entry_out[i]->expected_vbv = rcc->buffer_size - fills[i];
2902
2903 x264_free( fills-1 );
2904 return 0;
2905fail:
2906 return -1;
2907}
2908
2909static int init_pass2( x264_t *h )
2910{
2911 x264_ratecontrol_t *rcc = h->rc;
2912 uint64_t all_const_bits = 0;
2913 double timescale = (double)h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick / h->sps->vui.i_time_scale;
2914 double duration = 0;
2915 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
2916 duration += rcc->entry[i].i_duration;
2917 duration *= timescale;
2918 uint64_t all_available_bits = h->param.rc.i_bitrate * 1000. * duration;
2919 double rate_factor, step_mult;
2920 double qblur = h->param.rc.f_qblur;
2921 double cplxblur = h->param.rc.f_complexity_blur;
2922 const int filter_size = (int)(qblur*4) | 1;
2923 double expected_bits;
2924 double *qscale, *blurred_qscale;
2925 double base_cplx = h->mb.i_mb_count * (h->param.i_bframe ? 120 : 80);
2926
2927 /* find total/average complexity & const_bits */
2928 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
2929 {
2930 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = &rcc->entry[i];
2931 all_const_bits += rce->misc_bits;
2932 }
2933
2934 if( all_available_bits < all_const_bits)
2935 {
2936 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "requested bitrate is too low. estimated minimum is %d kbps\n",
2937 (int)(all_const_bits * rcc->fps / (rcc->num_entries * 1000.)) );
2938 return -1;
2939 }
2940
2941 /* Blur complexities, to reduce local fluctuation of QP.
2942 * We don't blur the QPs directly, because then one very simple frame
2943 * could drag down the QP of a nearby complex frame and give it more
2944 * bits than intended. */
2945 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
2946 {
2947 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = &rcc->entry[i];
2948 double weight_sum = 0;
2949 double cplx_sum = 0;
2950 double weight = 1.0;
2951 double gaussian_weight;
2952 /* weighted average of cplx of future frames */
2953 for( int j = 1; j < cplxblur*2 && j < rcc->num_entries-i; j++ )
2954 {
2955 ratecontrol_entry_t *rcj = &rcc->entry[i+j];
2956 double frame_duration = CLIP_DURATION(rcj->i_duration * timescale) / BASE_FRAME_DURATION;
2957 weight *= 1 - pow( (float)rcj->i_count / rcc->nmb, 2 );
2958 if( weight < .0001 )
2959 break;
2960 gaussian_weight = weight * exp( -j*j/200.0 );
2961 weight_sum += gaussian_weight;
2962 cplx_sum += gaussian_weight * (qscale2bits( rcj, 1 ) - rcj->misc_bits) / frame_duration;
2963 }
2964 /* weighted average of cplx of past frames */
2965 weight = 1.0;
2966 for( int j = 0; j <= cplxblur*2 && j <= i; j++ )
2967 {
2968 ratecontrol_entry_t *rcj = &rcc->entry[i-j];
2969 double frame_duration = CLIP_DURATION(rcj->i_duration * timescale) / BASE_FRAME_DURATION;
2970 gaussian_weight = weight * exp( -j*j/200.0 );
2971 weight_sum += gaussian_weight;
2972 cplx_sum += gaussian_weight * (qscale2bits( rcj, 1 ) - rcj->misc_bits) / frame_duration;
2973 weight *= 1 - pow( (float)rcj->i_count / rcc->nmb, 2 );
2974 if( weight < .0001 )
2975 break;
2976 }
2977 rce->blurred_complexity = cplx_sum / weight_sum;
2978 }
2979
2980 CHECKED_MALLOC( qscale, sizeof(double)*rcc->num_entries );
2981 if( filter_size > 1 )
2982 CHECKED_MALLOC( blurred_qscale, sizeof(double)*rcc->num_entries );
2983 else
2984 blurred_qscale = qscale;
2985
2986 /* Search for a factor which, when multiplied by the RCEQ values from
2987 * each frame, adds up to the desired total size.
2988 * There is no exact closed-form solution because of VBV constraints and
2989 * because qscale2bits is not invertible, but we can start with the simple
2990 * approximation of scaling the 1st pass by the ratio of bitrates.
2991 * The search range is probably overkill, but speed doesn't matter here. */
2992
2993 expected_bits = 1;
2994 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
2995 {
2996 double q = get_qscale(h, &rcc->entry[i], 1.0, i);
2997 expected_bits += qscale2bits(&rcc->entry[i], q);
2998 rcc->last_qscale_for[rcc->entry[i].pict_type] = q;
2999 }
3000 step_mult = all_available_bits / expected_bits;
3001
3002 rate_factor = 0;
3003 for( double step = 1E4 * step_mult; step > 1E-7 * step_mult; step *= 0.5)
3004 {
3005 expected_bits = 0;
3006 rate_factor += step;
3007
3008 rcc->last_non_b_pict_type = -1;
3009 rcc->last_accum_p_norm = 1;
3010 rcc->accum_p_norm = 0;
3011
3012 rcc->last_qscale_for[0] =
3013 rcc->last_qscale_for[1] =
3014 rcc->last_qscale_for[2] = pow( base_cplx, 1 - rcc->qcompress ) / rate_factor;
3015
3016 /* find qscale */
3017 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
3018 {
3019 qscale[i] = get_qscale( h, &rcc->entry[i], rate_factor, -1 );
3020 rcc->last_qscale_for[rcc->entry[i].pict_type] = qscale[i];
3021 }
3022
3023 /* fixed I/B qscale relative to P */
3024 for( int i = rcc->num_entries-1; i >= 0; i-- )
3025 {
3026 qscale[i] = get_diff_limited_q( h, &rcc->entry[i], qscale[i], i );
3027 assert(qscale[i] >= 0);
3028 }
3029
3030 /* smooth curve */
3031 if( filter_size > 1 )
3032 {
3033 assert( filter_size%2 == 1 );
3034 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
3035 {
3036 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = &rcc->entry[i];
3037 double q = 0.0, sum = 0.0;
3038
3039 for( int j = 0; j < filter_size; j++ )
3040 {
3041 int idx = i+j-filter_size/2;
3042 double d = idx-i;
3043 double coeff = qblur==0 ? 1.0 : exp( -d*d/(qblur*qblur) );
3044 if( idx < 0 || idx >= rcc->num_entries )
3045 continue;
3046 if( rce->pict_type != rcc->entry[idx].pict_type )
3047 continue;
3048 q += qscale[idx] * coeff;
3049 sum += coeff;
3050 }
3051 blurred_qscale[i] = q/sum;
3052 }
3053 }
3054
3055 /* find expected bits */
3056 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
3057 {
3058 ratecontrol_entry_t *rce = &rcc->entry[i];
3059 rce->new_qscale = clip_qscale( h, rce->pict_type, blurred_qscale[i] );
3060 assert(rce->new_qscale >= 0);
3061 expected_bits += qscale2bits( rce, rce->new_qscale );
3062 }
3063
3064 if( expected_bits > all_available_bits )
3065 rate_factor -= step;
3066 }
3067
3068 x264_free( qscale );
3069 if( filter_size > 1 )
3070 x264_free( blurred_qscale );
3071
3072 if( rcc->b_vbv )
3073 if( vbv_pass2( h, all_available_bits ) )
3074 return -1;
3075 expected_bits = count_expected_bits( h );
3076
3077 if( fabs( expected_bits/all_available_bits - 1.0 ) > 0.01 )
3078 {
3079 double avgq = 0;
3080 for( int i = 0; i < rcc->num_entries; i++ )
3081 avgq += rcc->entry[i].new_qscale;
3082 avgq = qscale2qp( avgq / rcc->num_entries );
3083
3084 if( expected_bits > all_available_bits || !rcc->b_vbv )
3085 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "Error: 2pass curve failed to converge\n" );
3086 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "target: %.2f kbit/s, expected: %.2f kbit/s, avg QP: %.4f\n",
3087 (float)h->param.rc.i_bitrate,
3088 expected_bits * rcc->fps / (rcc->num_entries * 1000.),
3089 avgq );
3090 if( expected_bits < all_available_bits && avgq < h->param.rc.i_qp_min + 2 )
3091 {
3092 if( h->param.rc.i_qp_min > 0 )
3093 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "try reducing target bitrate or reducing qp_min (currently %d)\n", h->param.rc.i_qp_min );
3094 else
3095 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "try reducing target bitrate\n" );
3096 }
3097 else if( expected_bits > all_available_bits && avgq > h->param.rc.i_qp_max - 2 )
3098 {
3099 if( h->param.rc.i_qp_max < QP_MAX )
3100 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "try increasing target bitrate or increasing qp_max (currently %d)\n", h->param.rc.i_qp_max );
3101 else
3102 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "try increasing target bitrate\n");
3103 }
3104 else if( !(rcc->b_2pass && rcc->b_vbv) )
3105 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "internal error\n" );
3106 }
3107
3108 return 0;
3109fail:
3110 return -1;
3111}
